WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:03.900
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

00:14.126 --> 00:16.860
[crowd cheering]

00:32.263 --> 00:34.132
Sir, one minute warning.

00:34.267 --> 00:35.524
Congratulations again.

00:35.660 --> 00:37.934
Heard anything from Betty,
from my daughter?

00:38.070 --> 00:40.174
No, sir.
We tried her several times.

00:40.309 --> 00:41.309
Okay.

00:41.444 --> 00:42.945
Thank you.

00:44.248 --> 00:46.419
[male announcer]
All right, New Hampshire,

00:46.555 --> 00:48.521
we are moments away.

00:48.657 --> 00:50.926
Are you ready?

00:51.062 --> 00:53.766
[crowd] Ready for Ross!
Ready for Ross!

00:53.901 --> 00:56.871
Ready for Ross!
Ready for Ross!

00:57.006 --> 01:00.011
Ready for Ross!
Ready for Ross!

01:00.148 --> 01:01.853
[male announcer]
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:01.988 --> 01:06.161
the next President of
the United States of America,

01:06.297 --> 01:08.430
Thaddeus Ross!

01:08.566 --> 01:10.803
[crowd applauds, cheers]

01:28.736 --> 01:30.171
Thank you.

01:31.712 --> 01:35.415
Tonight, America has spoken

01:35.551 --> 01:40.423
in one of the most important
elections of our lifetimes.

01:40.558 --> 01:44.538
We've recognized the urgency
of this moment.

01:44.874 --> 01:48.977
From the disappearance
of half of mankind

01:49.112 --> 01:52.143
to the emergence
of a celestial mass

01:52.279 --> 01:53.956
in the Indian Ocean,

01:54.092 --> 01:58.294
the threats we face show
no signs of slowing down.

01:58.430 --> 02:04.338
But the only way we can
overcome them is together!

02:05.074 --> 02:06.407
Tonight, President Ross

02:06.543 --> 02:08.209
embraced
the theme of togetherness

02:08.345 --> 02:09.578
in his acceptance speech,

02:09.714 --> 02:11.816
but his past
tells a different story,

02:11.951 --> 02:13.726
especially when it comes to
working with heroes

02:13.861 --> 02:15.227
like Captain America.

02:15.363 --> 02:17.671
As two of our nation's
most important leaders,

02:17.807 --> 02:19.708
some question
if they can overcome

02:19.844 --> 02:22.073
their at-times
tumultuous history

02:22.209 --> 02:23.945
to face the challenges ahead.

02:24.081 --> 02:25.648
[bartender] Here you go, Cap.

02:25.783 --> 02:27.251
[female reporter] During his
time as a four-star general...

02:27.387 --> 02:29.359
Put your money away.
It's on the house.

02:29.496 --> 02:30.593
[Sam chuckles]

02:30.728 --> 02:31.865
Thanks, Charlie.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.464
[female reporter]
...leading to Ross

02:33.600 --> 02:36.037
being branded with the moniker
of "the Hulk Hunter."

02:36.173 --> 02:37.873
Following Hulk
and the Abomination's

02:38.008 --> 02:39.276
destruction of Harlem,

02:39.411 --> 02:41.414
Ross was criticized
for what some called

02:41.550 --> 02:44.989
"an unwarranted outburst"
during a press conference.

02:45.491 --> 02:48.392
In fact, many blamed Ross
for the collateral damage,

02:48.528 --> 02:50.296
believing it was his
relentless pursuit

02:50.432 --> 02:53.106
of Banner's Hulk
that led to the rampage.

02:53.241 --> 02:55.504
It also resulted in
the President-elect's

02:55.641 --> 02:57.015
estrangement from his daughter,

02:57.150 --> 03:00.614
Dr. Betty Ross,
Bruce Banner's ex-girlfriend.

03:00.749 --> 03:02.122
But in a surprising turn
of events,

03:02.258 --> 03:03.763
he managed to
shift the narrative,

03:03.899 --> 03:05.734
and silence his harshest critics

03:05.870 --> 03:07.833
by apprehending
the man responsible

03:07.969 --> 03:09.405
for the Abomination.

03:09.675 --> 03:12.144
[alarm blares]

03:16.690 --> 03:19.819
[electrical buzzing]

03:30.442 --> 03:32.448
[jet engine roaring]

03:34.794 --> 03:37.889
[♪ dramatic music playing]

03:38.525 --> 03:39.732
How we lookin' down there?

03:39.869 --> 03:41.102
Well, SERPENT mercenaries

03:41.238 --> 03:42.864
entered with the package
about an hour ago.

03:43.000 --> 03:44.841
They're handing it
to the buyer any minute.

03:45.210 --> 03:46.442
We know what they're carrying?

03:46.578 --> 03:48.375
That is classified
per the White House.

03:48.511 --> 03:50.188
[sighs] Of course it is.

03:50.323 --> 03:52.257
Where's Eagle-One?
We have strike authorization.

03:52.392 --> 03:55.389
Eagle-One is entering
the target airspace now.

03:55.524 --> 03:57.729
[jet engine roars]

03:58.900 --> 04:00.809
Upload the compound's
covert entry points.

04:00.945 --> 04:03.874
Covert? Really?
You must be new.

04:10.755 --> 04:14.466
[♪ triumphant music playing]

04:15.365 --> 04:16.404
Wait for it.

04:33.472 --> 04:34.876
Sam, SEAL team
is six minutes out.

04:35.012 --> 04:36.180
[Captain America] Copy that.

04:53.909 --> 04:55.350
How the hell
did he just do that?

04:55.485 --> 04:57.051
Cap's gear was a gift
from the Wakandans

04:57.187 --> 04:58.622
for helping them out.

04:58.758 --> 05:01.263
I heard even the wrapping
paper was made of vibranium.

05:02.628 --> 05:05.172
No, man. I'm kidding. Come on.

05:08.545 --> 05:11.544
Joaquin, Redwing's pickin' up
hostages inside.

05:11.679 --> 05:13.084
- I'm goin' in.
- Negative.

05:13.220 --> 05:14.753
The package is the priority.

05:14.889 --> 05:15.989
[Captain America] Have the
SEALs track down the package.

05:16.125 --> 05:17.889
I'm on the hostages.

05:18.993 --> 05:21.370
Redwing, send them a scan
of the building.

05:21.772 --> 05:22.705
[speaks Spanish]

05:22.840 --> 05:24.099
What is it?

05:24.236 --> 05:25.846
That's Sidewinder.
He's the head of SERPENT.

05:25.982 --> 05:28.041
He's not supposed to be here.

05:30.583 --> 05:32.424
[hostages whimpering]

05:33.788 --> 05:35.630
[priest praying in Spanish]

05:35.766 --> 05:37.098
Ah.

05:37.234 --> 05:39.432
You're praying, Padre.

05:39.568 --> 05:43.005
[Sidewinder, in Spanish]

05:46.152 --> 05:47.321
- Padre.
- [groans]

05:47.457 --> 05:49.920
[priest continues
praying in Spanish]

05:53.266 --> 05:56.837
Padre. Padre, Padre, Padre.

05:56.973 --> 05:58.233
[sighs]

05:58.703 --> 06:01.383
[in Spanish]

06:12.171 --> 06:13.271
[in English] Kill them.

06:13.675 --> 06:15.679
- [hostage man] No. No!
- Kill them one at a time.

06:15.814 --> 06:17.441
[speaks Spanish]

06:17.576 --> 06:18.814
Silencio!

06:18.950 --> 06:19.687
[male mercenary on radio]
Captain America is here.

06:19.822 --> 06:20.514
Do you copy?

06:20.649 --> 06:22.319
Move, move, move!

06:22.455 --> 06:24.924
Vámonos, vámonos.

06:26.696 --> 06:28.470
Get the package outta here.

06:31.177 --> 06:33.281
[♪ tense music playing]

06:59.667 --> 07:01.326
SERPENT's on the move
with the canister, Sam.

07:01.462 --> 07:03.506
[Captain America]
I'm kinda busy right now!

07:11.893 --> 07:13.559
[grunting]

07:30.294 --> 07:32.663
Redwing, on my mark.

07:35.800 --> 07:37.035
[female mercenary] Stop.

07:38.544 --> 07:40.671
Stay back!
Or we'll shoot them.

07:40.907 --> 07:42.243
[in Spanish]

07:55.472 --> 07:57.547
SERPENT's gettin' farther away
with the canister, Sam,

07:57.683 --> 07:59.519
and Sidewinder's
headed to the chapel.

08:00.523 --> 08:02.017
I already know
what you're trying to do.

08:02.152 --> 08:04.155
You can't be at two places
at once.

08:05.023 --> 08:06.265
All right, this time.

08:06.401 --> 08:07.727
But don't get yourself killed.

08:07.864 --> 08:09.033
No dying. Copy that.

08:18.951 --> 08:20.361
Buyer didn't show.

08:20.497 --> 08:22.064
Looks like you need
better clients.

08:22.200 --> 08:23.896
You don't need to worry.

08:24.031 --> 08:26.062
I'll find whoever
wasted my time.

08:26.198 --> 08:27.870
You have bigger concerns.

08:28.007 --> 08:29.711
- [yells]
- [Captain America grunts]

08:31.777 --> 08:34.149
[both straining]

08:37.756 --> 08:39.159
[blows landing]

08:40.534 --> 08:42.264
[Captain America grunting]

08:44.639 --> 08:46.041
[groans, chuckles]

08:53.487 --> 08:55.229
The Captain America
I dreamt of killing

08:55.365 --> 08:56.297
was bigger than you.

08:56.433 --> 08:58.428
I'm happy to disappoint.

08:59.667 --> 09:00.872
[sighs]

09:01.509 --> 09:03.581
I bet you break easy.

09:04.151 --> 09:05.475
Not that easy.

09:18.135 --> 09:19.178
Not that hard.

09:19.314 --> 09:21.005
I heard your rib go.

09:21.141 --> 09:22.444
You need a minute?

09:22.579 --> 09:24.155
[pained] Nope. Nope,
let's get this over with.

09:24.291 --> 09:26.385
I got shit to do today.

09:41.686 --> 09:43.661
Whoo-hoo!

09:45.759 --> 09:46.693
Damn.

09:46.828 --> 09:48.363
Nobody saw that.

09:50.001 --> 09:52.172
Sam, package is secured.

09:53.908 --> 09:55.344
[both shout]

09:58.517 --> 10:00.695
I'll add your star
to my collection.

10:10.006 --> 10:10.840
[bone cracking]

10:10.976 --> 10:12.216
Need a minute?

10:12.352 --> 10:13.820
[groaning]

10:16.989 --> 10:18.290
That's what I thought.

10:23.466 --> 10:25.701
[♪ triumphant music playing]

10:33.186 --> 10:34.754
Save some for us, Cap.

10:35.558 --> 10:37.762
He has a fractured arm,
so be gentle.

10:37.897 --> 10:39.365
[chuckles]

10:45.050 --> 10:47.644
[Ross] "Keep your face
always to the sunshine,

10:47.780 --> 10:50.086
and the shadows
will fall behind you."

10:50.221 --> 10:52.522
The quote was Betty's idea.

10:52.657 --> 10:54.728
She's still not speaking
with you?

10:54.864 --> 10:56.034
No.

10:56.170 --> 10:58.371
She doesn't believe
I've changed.

10:58.741 --> 11:00.407
Really changed.

11:02.381 --> 11:04.683
I don't think I'm gonna get
another shot.

11:05.654 --> 11:08.589
Comin' up on the end of
my first hundred days, Leila.

11:10.029 --> 11:11.661
They're gonna define me.

11:13.300 --> 11:15.404
This treaty's gotta work.

11:15.940 --> 11:18.576
[phone vibrates]

11:20.112 --> 11:21.516
Hello.

11:21.652 --> 11:23.116
[major] Mr. President,
the mission was a success.

11:23.519 --> 11:24.785
[Ross] All right, fill me in.

11:25.121 --> 11:27.428
[major] Cap and the SEAL team
saved the hostages.

11:27.563 --> 11:30.363
The package is secure
and en route to the US.

11:30.834 --> 11:32.003
[Captain America]
How's your brother?

11:32.139 --> 11:33.502
Oh, wow, you remembered.

11:33.639 --> 11:35.247
- He's in the Air Force.
- Yeah?

11:35.383 --> 11:37.347
- Probably 'cause of you.
- [Captain America laughs]

11:37.483 --> 11:39.215
I try not to hold that
against him.

11:39.350 --> 11:40.385
It's a weird place

11:40.520 --> 11:41.958
- for a handoff, right?
- Mm-hmm.

11:42.094 --> 11:43.997
Wide open, soft perimeter.

11:44.532 --> 11:46.561
You think the buyer
ever intended on showin' up?

11:46.698 --> 11:48.168
You think SERPENT got played?

11:48.303 --> 11:49.503
What are they sayin'?

11:49.639 --> 11:51.510
Same thing.
Contract was anonymous.

11:51.645 --> 11:54.679
Fifty mil to steal the
canister en route to Japan.

11:54.816 --> 11:56.787
Then show up here
and meet the buyer.

11:57.156 --> 11:58.358
[Captain America] Hmm.

12:00.058 --> 12:02.969
Let us know if you get a trace
on Sidewinder.

12:03.104 --> 12:04.667
- Good work.
- Thank you.

12:09.083 --> 12:11.615
You'll notice, I did not die,

12:11.750 --> 12:13.922
and people are saying
I did not die in style.

12:14.058 --> 12:15.155
Who is saying that?

12:15.524 --> 12:16.589
- People.
- What people?

12:16.724 --> 12:17.832
- Everybody.
- [chuckles]

12:17.968 --> 12:19.400
Everybody is saying that.

12:19.802 --> 12:22.240
Look, tell me I don't make
your old gear look brand-new.

12:22.376 --> 12:24.844
You've got on the greaves
upside down.

12:24.979 --> 12:26.111
I'm joking.

12:26.247 --> 12:27.553
You look good, man.

12:27.689 --> 12:29.118
All right. Fair enough.

12:29.488 --> 12:30.383
That means that
you're finally gonna

12:30.519 --> 12:31.592
introduce me to Ant-Man?

12:31.727 --> 12:32.857
Nope.

12:33.661 --> 12:34.832
Well, at least
you gotta teach me

12:34.968 --> 12:36.403
your aerial kick, man.

12:36.539 --> 12:39.174
Look, if I'm gonna be Falcon,
I gotta know everything.

12:39.309 --> 12:40.872
In no way
are you ready for that.

12:41.008 --> 12:43.013
But I got a guy who'll
teach you the fundamentals

12:43.149 --> 12:44.047
from the ground up.

12:44.182 --> 12:45.151
Absolutely.

12:45.287 --> 12:46.884
Now, he's not a people person.

12:47.020 --> 12:48.991
So you gotta learn
how to keep your mouth shut.

12:49.126 --> 12:50.429
Can you do that?

12:51.437 --> 12:52.697
[sighs]

12:52.832 --> 12:54.471
He's gonna love me, bro!
Are you kidding me?

12:54.607 --> 12:56.601
- That's not the right answer.
- He's gonna love me.

12:56.737 --> 12:58.974
[♪ "Ante Up" playing]

13:02.449 --> 13:03.756
[song fades]

13:03.892 --> 13:04.628
What's up, OG?

13:04.763 --> 13:06.021
Who's the pretty boy?

13:06.156 --> 13:07.930
"Pretty boy"? You didn't
tell gramps about me?

13:08.067 --> 13:09.068
I'm the new Falcon.

13:09.203 --> 13:10.562
- No, you're not.
- Yes, I am.

13:10.698 --> 13:12.472
This is Joaquin Torres.

13:12.608 --> 13:14.114
Been workin' with him
for three years.

13:14.249 --> 13:16.007
I haven't figured out
how to shut him up yet.

13:16.144 --> 13:18.614
So what are we doing here?
Orthopedics? Uh...

13:19.117 --> 13:21.887
How to relearn how to walk
after you break a hip?

13:25.031 --> 13:26.402
Oh, sh...

13:27.873 --> 13:29.107
Oh, shit.

13:29.242 --> 13:30.471
[Sam] That's Isaiah Bradley.

13:30.607 --> 13:32.981
The... The Isaiah Bradley?

13:33.484 --> 13:35.019
You brought me to
the forgotten Cap?

13:35.156 --> 13:36.121
Why didn't you say something?

13:36.257 --> 13:37.918
It is a pleasure to meet you.

13:38.053 --> 13:40.627
Your missions in Korea
are legendary.

13:40.762 --> 13:42.267
And what, and after that,
no action?

13:42.403 --> 13:43.632
I mean, a lot's changed
in the world.

13:43.768 --> 13:45.205
We could've used
another super soldier.

13:45.340 --> 13:46.473
The United States government

13:46.609 --> 13:48.642
threw me in prison for 30 years.

13:48.778 --> 13:52.048
They experimented on me
for decades.

13:52.585 --> 13:54.286
Yikes, that's... that sucks.

13:54.422 --> 13:55.728
Can we start?

13:55.863 --> 13:56.456
Let's do it.

13:56.592 --> 13:58.499
No vibranium wings,

13:59.403 --> 14:02.705
no shield,
no super soldier serum.

14:04.040 --> 14:06.381
I wanna see
if he's got three in him.

14:06.517 --> 14:08.349
[Joaquin]
Get those flags, Sam!

14:08.485 --> 14:09.316
[♪ "Elephant" playing]

14:09.451 --> 14:10.886
Cap v Cap!

14:11.389 --> 14:12.527
[exclaims]

14:14.031 --> 14:15.092
[Joaquin whoops]

14:17.071 --> 14:18.003
[Sam] That's one.

14:18.138 --> 14:18.939
[Joaquin claps]

14:19.074 --> 14:20.270
Let's go!

14:20.807 --> 14:22.415
[Joaquin exclaims] Orthopedic.

14:26.925 --> 14:28.021
That's two.

14:28.157 --> 14:29.660
[laughs]

14:35.101 --> 14:37.845
I'm sorry.
What were you sayin'?

14:38.214 --> 14:39.914
See? Not a people person.

14:40.049 --> 14:43.188
- In a fight, the last hit...
- Is the only hit that matters.

14:43.323 --> 14:44.822
I know. Shut up, but thanks.

14:44.958 --> 14:46.959
All right, that's it.
Tag me in. I'm ready.

14:47.094 --> 14:50.603
Captain America doesn't
get to take five. Let's go.

14:51.338 --> 14:52.970
I need to take this.

14:53.640 --> 14:55.139
I'm not takin' five.

14:58.379 --> 15:01.460
- You still got the plastic on.
- No! I don't...

15:02.692 --> 15:04.491
Maybe I wanted it on there.

15:05.194 --> 15:07.036
Oh, you want me
to make the text bigger?

15:07.172 --> 15:08.571
So you can read it?

15:08.706 --> 15:10.643
Yeah, I'll hold
for the President.

15:19.095 --> 15:20.431
Where you going?

15:23.402 --> 15:24.704
You wanna talk about it?

15:28.074 --> 15:31.619
It just doesn't
sit right with me.

15:31.755 --> 15:35.121
Captain America,
answering to the President.

15:35.256 --> 15:38.032
The President of the country
who stole your life?

15:38.168 --> 15:39.569
It's not just that.

15:39.705 --> 15:42.839
We're talkin' about
Thaddeus "Thunderbolt" Ross.

15:42.974 --> 15:44.808
Son of a bitch
earned that nickname, too.

15:44.944 --> 15:46.978
Look, I know, Isaiah, firsthand.

15:47.113 --> 15:49.621
Remember,
Ross threw me in the Raft.

15:49.757 --> 15:51.953
Hounded me, Steve and Natasha
for years.

15:52.088 --> 15:53.389
So why are you workin' for him?

15:53.525 --> 15:54.328
[sighs]

15:54.463 --> 15:55.799
As long as you do,

15:55.934 --> 15:58.905
Captain America
stands for people like him.

15:59.040 --> 16:01.544
You've got no business
workin' for the government.

16:01.679 --> 16:03.650
You see what's going on
out there?

16:04.187 --> 16:06.055
The country is lost.

16:06.490 --> 16:08.059
Standing next to the President,

16:08.195 --> 16:09.628
even if it's Ross...

16:10.331 --> 16:12.097
it gives people hope.

16:12.934 --> 16:14.573
Now, come on,
give me some credit.

16:14.708 --> 16:16.402
I have a friend who works
in the White House.

16:16.537 --> 16:19.847
She'll let me know if Ross
starts acting out of turn.

16:21.688 --> 16:24.020
None of this means
I forgot about you.

16:25.361 --> 16:26.864
I see what you're doin'.

16:26.999 --> 16:28.059
What?

16:28.195 --> 16:29.902
Pullin' that counseling
bullshit on me.

16:30.038 --> 16:31.705
[laughs]

16:32.175 --> 16:33.168
Look, trust me.

16:33.304 --> 16:35.511
My eyes are wide open
on this, okay?

16:35.647 --> 16:38.719
I know Ross will never change,

16:39.719 --> 16:41.825
but he is the President.

16:42.729 --> 16:43.893
So you gonna tell me
what he wanted

16:44.029 --> 16:46.031
or are you plannin' on
makin' me guess?

16:47.333 --> 16:49.772
He invited Joaquin and I
to the White House,

16:49.908 --> 16:52.140
and I said under one condition.

16:52.442 --> 16:55.181
If he extended an invitation
to you as well.

16:56.083 --> 16:57.584
I know you're gonna say no,

16:58.521 --> 17:00.929
but it would mean a lot to me
if you were there.

17:01.863 --> 17:03.331
- We just...
- [sighs]

17:03.734 --> 17:05.404
...gotta get you a suit.

17:05.540 --> 17:07.143
I have a damn suit.

17:07.278 --> 17:08.578
For real?

17:08.713 --> 17:09.710
Then why are you always wearin'

17:09.846 --> 17:11.752
that ratty-ass sweatsuit?

17:12.386 --> 17:13.456
[laughs]

17:13.592 --> 17:15.595
Come on, you gonna come or what?

17:19.002 --> 17:21.833
[♪ hip-hop playing,
Blackway "Get It Done"]

17:22.503 --> 17:24.174
[Sam] See, Isaiah? This is
what I'm talking about.

17:24.310 --> 17:26.947
Now you're going to
the White House. Look at that.

17:27.083 --> 17:28.710
- You look good, OG.
- [Joaquin] Wow, man.

17:28.846 --> 17:30.257
I told you I was gonna get you
out of those sweats.

17:30.392 --> 17:31.825
Look at you now, man.

17:31.960 --> 17:34.327
I didn't know Men's Warehouse
made that size.

17:34.463 --> 17:35.666
[laughs]

17:35.802 --> 17:37.904
Hey, Faith and I
got married in this.

17:38.039 --> 17:39.672
- Okay, all right, all right.
- [Isaiah chuckles]

17:39.807 --> 17:40.935
I'm sure she would be proud.

17:41.070 --> 17:42.377
I hope so.

17:43.448 --> 17:46.490
Feels strange to walk right
into the belly of the beast.

17:46.626 --> 17:47.818
Hey, I'm sure it can't be easy.

17:47.953 --> 17:49.088
[Isaiah] It ain't.

17:49.225 --> 17:50.564
Which is why we gotta celebrate.

17:50.700 --> 17:52.328
I don't care
if it is Ross in charge.

17:52.463 --> 17:54.365
We are guests of honor
at the White House, man!

17:54.500 --> 17:55.968
- When does that ever happen?
- [Sam] Right.

17:56.104 --> 17:57.572
And they sent us a limo, man.

17:57.707 --> 17:59.005
What?

17:59.140 --> 18:00.616
And we look good.

18:00.751 --> 18:02.017
- [Joaquin] Yeah.
- [Sam] What?

18:02.152 --> 18:03.621
Old school,
you got your smell-good on.

18:03.756 --> 18:04.889
- What?
- [Joaquin laughs]

18:05.025 --> 18:06.820
And you got the houndstooth on.

18:07.324 --> 18:09.125
And we got the good stuff.

18:09.262 --> 18:11.306
It's party time. [laughs]

18:11.441 --> 18:13.678
[♪ song continues]

18:21.826 --> 18:23.092
[photographer 1]
Captain America!

18:23.227 --> 18:24.997
[photographer 2]
Captain, Captain, over here.

18:25.132 --> 18:27.504
- Cap, over here!
- [photographer 3] Mr. Bradley.

18:27.639 --> 18:28.772
[photographer 2] Over here!

18:28.908 --> 18:30.200
- Hey, Isaiah. Check it out.
- Oh.

18:30.337 --> 18:32.848
[photographers clamoring]

18:37.889 --> 18:41.899
Whoa, man, look at this!

18:43.703 --> 18:45.405
Oh, we gotta get a pic.

18:45.540 --> 18:46.777
Let's do it.

18:48.614 --> 18:49.876
Tres amigos on three.

18:50.012 --> 18:52.121
Uno, dos, tres. Ah!

18:52.256 --> 18:53.657
[chuckles]

18:54.127 --> 18:55.826
[Joaquin] Yeah, that's my
new wallpaper. Look at that.

18:55.962 --> 18:56.992
- [Isaiah] Pretty good.
- It's good?

18:57.127 --> 18:58.359
[Isaiah]
Can you send it to me?

18:58.496 --> 18:59.900
Yeah, I'll AirDrop it to you
right now.

19:00.036 --> 19:01.563
You do know
what AirDrop is, right?

19:01.698 --> 19:03.642
Of course,
I know what AirDrop is.

19:03.778 --> 19:05.643
- What's AirDrop?
- [laughs]

19:06.045 --> 19:07.145
You see, you should have it.

19:07.280 --> 19:08.810
Just hit "Accept"
and it pops up.

19:08.946 --> 19:11.583
- [Isaiah] I did that.
- Excuse me, gentlemen.

19:11.719 --> 19:13.722
The President
needs Mr. Wilson.

19:14.358 --> 19:16.099
I'll see you guys inside.

19:17.033 --> 19:17.967
- Hey.
- Hey.

19:18.102 --> 19:19.509
Sam, just keep an open mind.

19:19.644 --> 19:21.274
Why? What am I walking into?

19:21.409 --> 19:23.783
Thi... This is not
the picture you took.

19:23.919 --> 19:25.345
Oh, I sent you
the wrong picture.

19:25.480 --> 19:26.522
- Oh, my Lord.
- [laughs]

19:27.058 --> 19:29.185
[Ross] Well,
that's a very good point.

19:29.320 --> 19:30.358
I'll consider it.

19:31.157 --> 19:32.264
Wilson.

19:33.135 --> 19:35.170
Folks, can you give us the room?

19:37.202 --> 19:38.209
Uh...

19:38.712 --> 19:40.015
[chuckles]

19:40.417 --> 19:41.314
Thanks.

19:42.279 --> 19:43.680
Doctor's orders.

19:44.082 --> 19:47.121
Not quite a cigar,
but better than that damn gum.

19:47.256 --> 19:47.993
[Sam] Hmm.

19:48.128 --> 19:49.357
Thanks for comin' in.

19:49.627 --> 19:50.837
Welcome to the White House.

19:50.973 --> 19:52.503
Well, thank you
for the invite, sir.

19:52.640 --> 19:55.938
I have to admit, I'm still
gettin' used to the new look.

19:56.073 --> 19:59.951
[chuckles] Yeah, well,
they said lose the mustache

20:00.086 --> 20:01.784
or lose the election.

20:03.393 --> 20:05.365
Thanks for your help
down in Mexico.

20:05.500 --> 20:09.774
Retrieving that canister might
just have saved this treaty.

20:09.910 --> 20:11.736
I was just doing my job, sir.

20:11.872 --> 20:13.313
You and I haven't always agreed

20:13.449 --> 20:17.514
on how much latitude
enhanced individuals deserve.

20:17.649 --> 20:19.124
But what you've accomplished

20:19.259 --> 20:21.493
has given me reason
to reconsider.

20:22.431 --> 20:26.600
Which is why I want you,
Captain America,

20:26.737 --> 20:30.049
to help me rebuild the Avengers.

20:31.150 --> 20:33.154
- The Avengers?
- Yes, sir.

20:37.197 --> 20:39.362
Well, with all due respect, sir,

20:39.498 --> 20:42.003
when you passed
the Sokovia Accords,

20:42.138 --> 20:43.509
you tore the Avengers apart.

20:43.645 --> 20:44.601
Why the change of heart?

20:44.737 --> 20:47.743
I represent all Americans now.

20:49.156 --> 20:51.724
Hell, half of 'em
wouldn't even be here

20:51.860 --> 20:53.425
without the Avengers.

20:54.866 --> 20:56.501
The country needs this.

20:57.338 --> 21:00.241
And when we disagree on
how to manage a situation...

21:01.812 --> 21:03.282
what happens then?

21:03.818 --> 21:05.185
We figure it out together.

21:07.159 --> 21:09.426
Look, you don't have to
give me an answer now.

21:09.895 --> 21:11.494
Just think about it.

21:17.812 --> 21:19.046
Prime Minister Ozaki.

21:19.181 --> 21:20.749
- Great to see you, sir.
- And you.

21:20.885 --> 21:22.285
Thank you for being here.

21:24.923 --> 21:26.093
Here we are.

21:26.229 --> 21:28.599
Sam Wilson,
Prime Minister Ozaki.

21:28.734 --> 21:30.829
[speaks Japanese]

21:31.972 --> 21:33.665
Not bad. [chuckles]

21:33.801 --> 21:34.840
Would you like a picture?

21:34.975 --> 21:35.843
Sure.

21:35.978 --> 21:37.381
Sam, please.

21:39.256 --> 21:41.092
[photographer 4]
Stand a little bit closer.

21:42.888 --> 21:44.360
- Thank you, gentlemen.
- Thank you.

21:44.495 --> 21:46.201
- Thank you.
- [speaks Japanese]

21:48.136 --> 21:49.365
Work with me, Sam.

21:50.135 --> 21:52.378
We'll show the world
a better way forward.

21:58.619 --> 22:00.091
That was unexpected.

22:00.228 --> 22:02.167
Maybe it's an opportunity.

22:07.909 --> 22:09.104
So?

22:09.507 --> 22:10.445
How was it?

22:10.581 --> 22:12.552
He asked me
to restart the Avengers.

22:13.222 --> 22:14.420
- Wait, what now?
- [chuckles]

22:14.556 --> 22:16.426
- That's huge, man.
- I don't know.

22:17.196 --> 22:18.595
We'd have to work for him.

22:18.730 --> 22:20.369
[male announcer 2]
Ladies and gentlemen,

22:20.505 --> 22:23.438
the President of the
United States, Thaddeus Ross.

22:23.574 --> 22:26.380
Good evening, everyone.
Good evening.

22:27.615 --> 22:30.256
It's my great privilege
to host you

22:30.392 --> 22:33.494
at the White House
on this historic evening.

22:33.629 --> 22:38.602
When the celestial mass
emerged in the Indian Ocean,

22:39.272 --> 22:41.944
we did what we often do.

22:42.079 --> 22:44.009
We squabbled over it.

22:44.144 --> 22:47.446
Countries rushed in
to claim it as their own,

22:47.582 --> 22:52.593
setting up research facilities
to exploit its resources.

22:52.729 --> 22:53.861
[♪ pensive music playing]

22:53.997 --> 22:55.571
What was found
inside that island

22:55.706 --> 22:59.044
is nothing short of the
discovery of the millennium.

22:59.747 --> 23:03.582
Its potential applications
in tech, in medicine,

23:03.717 --> 23:06.554
in defense are immeasurable.

23:07.156 --> 23:11.166
It's even more indestructible
than vibranium.

23:11.870 --> 23:15.643
And it's not controlled
by an isolationist nation.

23:16.907 --> 23:18.445
Ladies and gentlemen,

23:18.581 --> 23:20.245
I present to you...

23:20.891 --> 23:22.359
adamantium.

23:26.369 --> 23:29.669
The first and only
refined sample

23:29.805 --> 23:32.372
was stolen from
a Japanese mining site.

23:32.508 --> 23:33.713
But happily,

23:33.848 --> 23:36.687
it's been recovered
and is in a secure location.

23:36.823 --> 23:41.598
And we have two incredibly
brave men to thank for that.

23:41.734 --> 23:46.672
Joaquin Torres and our own
Captain America, Sam Wilson.

23:57.630 --> 24:01.136
What we do next
with this discovery

24:01.505 --> 24:04.878
will determine
how history judges us.

24:05.180 --> 24:06.612
If we ratify this treaty,

24:06.748 --> 24:10.251
together we can produce
enough adamantium

24:10.387 --> 24:12.083
to fairly and equitably

24:12.219 --> 24:13.695
distribute it around the world.

24:13.831 --> 24:15.188
[♪ The Fleetwoods "Mr. Blue"
playing over speakers]

24:15.324 --> 24:17.035
♪ I'm Mr. Blue
Wa-oo-wa-oo ♪

24:17.171 --> 24:18.334
Sir, you need to sit down.

24:18.470 --> 24:19.973
♪ When you say... ♪

24:20.108 --> 24:21.500
[song stops]

24:21.635 --> 24:23.944
- [guests clamoring]
- Isaiah! What are you doing?

24:25.012 --> 24:26.487
- [guest screams]
- [grunts]

24:32.098 --> 24:33.325
Sam!

24:39.579 --> 24:41.049
- Sir, are you hit?
- No.

24:41.185 --> 24:43.114
[agent] Go, go, go!

24:45.026 --> 24:46.186
[gunshot]

24:46.790 --> 24:48.498
[all speaking Japanese]

24:55.843 --> 24:57.406
- [gunshots]
- [guests scream]

25:00.819 --> 25:02.284
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

25:03.825 --> 25:05.763
Mr. President, come with me.

25:06.662 --> 25:07.668
[both grunting]

25:18.360 --> 25:21.355
[♪ dramatic music playing]

25:37.657 --> 25:38.697
Shit.

25:48.944 --> 25:50.721
[horn honks]

25:53.194 --> 25:54.095
Isaiah!

25:54.230 --> 25:57.031
[siren blaring]

26:08.460 --> 26:10.288
[police shouting indistinctly]

26:11.490 --> 26:13.734
- Get on the ground now!
- Do not move.

26:18.279 --> 26:19.806
What's happening?

26:20.343 --> 26:23.010
I don't know.
But you gotta stop.

26:23.147 --> 26:25.223
[officers clamoring]

26:25.892 --> 26:27.696
- [lead agent] Stop!
- [Sam] Don't!

26:31.472 --> 26:34.433
I can't go back inside, Sam.

26:34.569 --> 26:37.342
Run, and it'll be
worse than that.

26:41.114 --> 26:43.089
Please, Isaiah.

26:58.017 --> 26:59.158
Hey, take it easy!

26:59.295 --> 27:01.726
Watch my suit.

27:01.861 --> 27:05.133
Please, watch my suit.

27:12.983 --> 27:14.680
[♪ tense music playing]

27:18.895 --> 27:20.593
Cap, I can't let you in.

27:21.832 --> 27:22.995
Hey!

27:23.131 --> 27:24.603
Sam!

27:24.738 --> 27:27.243
- Sir, you can't... you can't...
- [card scanner beeps]

27:27.943 --> 27:29.046
Sir!

27:29.449 --> 27:31.520
- [Leila] Sorry, Mr. President.
- Hey, hey, hey.

27:31.655 --> 27:32.754
He stays.

27:32.890 --> 27:34.456
Everybody else, out.

27:41.007 --> 27:42.769
[Ross] Agent Taylor, you too.

27:49.251 --> 27:50.624
Are you okay?

27:51.260 --> 27:53.061
I should be asking
you that, sir.

27:53.197 --> 27:54.626
Not my first time being shot at.

27:54.762 --> 27:56.239
Look, I know how
this must look, but...

27:56.374 --> 27:57.700
[door opens]

27:59.404 --> 28:00.849
Can we have a minute?

28:02.684 --> 28:03.712
She stays.

28:05.454 --> 28:09.261
Meet Ruth Bat-Seraph,
my security advisor.

28:11.798 --> 28:13.875
Sir, there's no way
Isaiah could have done this.

28:14.010 --> 28:15.908
- Except he did.
- Maybe somebody got to him.

28:16.044 --> 28:17.376
You're really defending a man

28:17.512 --> 28:19.346
who just tried to kill
the President in front...

28:19.482 --> 28:22.651
- We don't know what happened.
- Enough.

28:24.761 --> 28:25.694
What do we know?

28:26.063 --> 28:26.928
There were five shooters.

28:27.064 --> 28:28.530
Isaiah was one of them.

28:28.666 --> 28:30.667
As was Secret Service
and active military.

28:30.803 --> 28:33.575
This was a coordinated
terrorist attack, sir.

28:33.712 --> 28:34.741
[sighs]

28:39.418 --> 28:40.418
What else do you have?

28:40.821 --> 28:42.259
The song
that preceded the shooting,

28:42.395 --> 28:43.825
we think it was a cue
for the attack.

28:43.960 --> 28:45.935
Sir, Isaiah looked like
he wasn't in control.

28:46.070 --> 28:47.464
He had no idea where he was.

28:47.600 --> 28:49.336
So you're suggesting what?

28:49.472 --> 28:50.775
[Sam] Let me investigate.

28:50.911 --> 28:52.150
[scoffs]

28:52.285 --> 28:53.878
Don't you think you're
a little too close to this?

28:54.014 --> 28:55.948
Sir, your inner circle
has been compromised.

28:56.083 --> 28:58.291
There's possibility
of another attack now.

28:58.427 --> 28:59.958
And what exactly
do you have to offer

29:00.094 --> 29:02.663
that our entire intelligence
and defense apparatus can't?

29:02.800 --> 29:04.371
Well, I won't sit around
and let Isaiah...

29:04.507 --> 29:08.109
Look, I know how important
Bradley is to you.

29:08.245 --> 29:10.153
But consider the optics.

29:11.157 --> 29:14.624
Captain America conducts
a personal investigation

29:14.759 --> 29:18.433
of a friend who tried
to assassinate the President.

29:18.568 --> 29:21.466
Isaiah sacrificed everything
for this country.

29:21.602 --> 29:23.912
He's a soldier. A patriot.

29:24.047 --> 29:25.275
He had no reason to do this.

29:25.411 --> 29:26.978
He had every reason.

29:27.113 --> 29:29.483
Bradley was in prison
for rescuing his own men,

29:29.619 --> 29:31.890
experimented on for 30 years.

29:32.026 --> 29:34.932
The things done to him are
enough to make anyone snap.

29:35.502 --> 29:37.438
Sir, you invited me here
to work together.

29:37.574 --> 29:40.342
- So let's work together.
- I'm afraid that offer expired

29:40.478 --> 29:42.546
when your friend tried
to kill me.

29:45.086 --> 29:46.118
[Ross sighs]

29:46.955 --> 29:51.663
Sam, you shouldn't even be
in these situations.

29:52.267 --> 29:55.341
You're not Steve Rogers.

29:57.813 --> 29:59.076
Ruth,

29:59.211 --> 30:01.347
you have my full authority
to put this thing to bed.

30:02.117 --> 30:04.986
Before this treaty
gets compromised any further.

30:08.430 --> 30:09.666
So that's it?

30:10.906 --> 30:11.901
I'm done?

30:12.437 --> 30:13.507
You're done.

30:13.643 --> 30:15.782
This is bullshit,
and you know it.

30:15.917 --> 30:17.244
This is politics.

30:17.813 --> 30:20.016
So you better wise up, son.

30:22.230 --> 30:23.692
"Son." Who you calling "son"?

30:23.828 --> 30:25.660
Sam. What the hell
are you doing?

30:25.796 --> 30:26.997
I'm going to clear Isaiah.

30:27.133 --> 30:28.570
Storming in there
ain't gonna help him.

30:28.706 --> 30:30.873
- You need Ross on your side.
- Ross?

30:31.343 --> 30:32.479
Open your eyes.

30:32.615 --> 30:33.945
I offer to help,
and he sends me packin'.

30:34.080 --> 30:36.787
Ross is on his own side.
He always has been.

30:36.922 --> 30:39.089
Either you can't see that,
or you don't want to.

30:39.226 --> 30:40.332
Hey.

30:41.199 --> 30:42.166
Don't be that guy.

30:42.301 --> 30:43.765
And what guy is that?

30:43.901 --> 30:45.804
The one who has to do it
the hard way.

30:52.057 --> 30:53.888
Looks like I am that guy.

30:54.492 --> 30:56.892
[♪ dramatic music playing]

31:16.770 --> 31:18.905
[reporter] The nation remains
on high alert.

31:19.041 --> 31:22.039
The Justice Department has
signaled a death penalty case

31:22.175 --> 31:25.052
will be pursued
against Isaiah Bradley.

31:25.188 --> 31:26.985
Just five minutes, Cap.

31:29.696 --> 31:32.000
I could be court-martialed
for this.

31:32.136 --> 31:33.232
I appreciate it, Payumo.

31:33.368 --> 31:34.605
Yes, sir.

31:39.852 --> 31:40.577
[sighs]

31:40.713 --> 31:42.048
[door clanks]

32:00.820 --> 32:02.728
How you holdin' up?

32:03.364 --> 32:05.502
Not so good, brother Sam.

32:06.432 --> 32:07.671
Isaiah.

32:08.506 --> 32:09.774
Look me in the eye.

32:09.909 --> 32:11.706
Tell me you didn't
conspire to kill Ross.

32:11.842 --> 32:13.050
Of course I didn't.

32:13.186 --> 32:14.243
What in the world happened

32:14.378 --> 32:15.856
to make you shoot
at the President?

32:15.992 --> 32:17.085
I don't know.

32:17.220 --> 32:19.027
You gotta give me more
than "I don't know."

32:19.631 --> 32:21.733
Is there anything you remember?

32:22.135 --> 32:23.362
I got a haircut,

32:23.498 --> 32:26.070
picked my suit up at
the cleaners and came to you.

32:27.577 --> 32:29.583
We rode in the limo,

32:31.087 --> 32:32.452
took our photo.

32:32.589 --> 32:35.892
But my phone was on the fritz.

32:36.027 --> 32:39.966
And then, we went over
to the East Room.

32:41.375 --> 32:42.740
One moment I'm sittin' there,

32:42.875 --> 32:45.108
the next I'm standin'
in that park.

32:46.818 --> 32:49.484
I should have stayed
in my damn house,

32:49.620 --> 32:51.126
minded my business.

32:51.261 --> 32:52.161
No, this isn't on you.

32:52.297 --> 32:53.699
Someone's behind all this.

32:53.834 --> 32:58.002
Sam, the last thing I want
is for this to touch you.

32:59.408 --> 33:02.483
[breathes shakily]

33:05.750 --> 33:07.152
Besides...

33:11.692 --> 33:15.234
Look, there ain't no escapin'
for me this time.

33:16.906 --> 33:18.706
I'm gonna die in here.

33:18.842 --> 33:20.547
No, you're not.

33:20.682 --> 33:22.116
I'm gonna get you out.

33:26.566 --> 33:28.998
- You wanna help me?
- Of course.

33:31.174 --> 33:32.341
Don't come back.

33:32.477 --> 33:34.745
[♪ dramatic music playing]

33:37.515 --> 33:38.753
Guard.

33:56.256 --> 33:59.289
[Ruth] Sergeant Payumo, get me
a copy of that conversation.

34:00.466 --> 34:01.528
I wanna take another look.

34:01.663 --> 34:02.631
Yes, ma'am.

34:02.767 --> 34:04.672
And good work with Wilson.

34:04.808 --> 34:07.243
Let me know
if he pays another visit.

34:07.378 --> 34:08.615
Roger that.

34:11.552 --> 34:13.021
[Sam] You get in?

34:13.156 --> 34:14.727
[Joaquin] I think I committed
treason and espionage,

34:14.862 --> 34:17.826
but I made it into
the White House's CCTV system.

34:17.961 --> 34:19.330
What am I lookin' for?

34:19.465 --> 34:21.067
[Sam] When Isaiah went off
in the White House,

34:21.203 --> 34:23.005
it made me think
of a friend of mine.

34:23.142 --> 34:25.208
He was being controlled
by trigger words.

34:25.344 --> 34:27.379
Do you see any strangers
talkin' to Isaiah?

34:27.515 --> 34:30.251
[Joaquin] No, well,
we got there, took a picture,

34:30.387 --> 34:32.323
I AirDropped it to him,
but nothin' crazy.

34:32.458 --> 34:34.728
Yeah, but he said his phone
was on the fritz.

34:34.863 --> 34:35.863
Ah. Whoa, whoa, whoa.

34:35.999 --> 34:37.596
Sam, I think I got something.

34:38.606 --> 34:39.840
[Sam] What is it?

34:39.976 --> 34:42.606
His phone is like
flashing at him.

34:44.854 --> 34:46.390
Oh, shit, I got
the same thing happening

34:46.526 --> 34:47.990
to one of the other shooters.

35:10.703 --> 35:12.842
What the hell?

35:16.915 --> 35:19.014
Warden Cooper, Ross here.

35:19.150 --> 35:20.890
The prisoner, he's secure?

35:21.026 --> 35:23.960
I can confirm the prisoner
is in his cell.

35:24.095 --> 35:25.664
Do we have eyes on the bastard?

35:25.799 --> 35:26.967
[Ross] Personally.

35:27.102 --> 35:28.538
I'm looking at him
right now, sir.

35:28.673 --> 35:30.008
Thank you, Cooper.

35:31.549 --> 35:33.378
Thank you, Mr. President.

35:39.425 --> 35:41.730
[Sam]
I keep goin' back to Mexico.

35:41.866 --> 35:42.933
We were at the White House

35:43.069 --> 35:44.505
because the buyer never showed.

35:45.308 --> 35:48.904
Why hire SERPENT if you have
no intention on collecting?

35:49.040 --> 35:50.875
Maybe they were expecting
Captain America to come.

35:51.011 --> 35:53.253
[Sam] What if the buyer wanted
Captain America to come?

35:53.389 --> 35:54.892
And what if they wanted us
at the White House?

35:55.028 --> 35:56.430
[Joaquin] But how would
the buyer predict

35:56.566 --> 35:58.094
that we'd get the invite,

35:58.230 --> 36:00.002
or that you would invite Isaiah?

36:00.137 --> 36:02.338
[Sam] The buyer must be
watching us somehow.

36:02.708 --> 36:04.009
Another thing.

36:04.144 --> 36:08.009
Ruth Bat-Seraph,
Ross' security advisor,

36:08.747 --> 36:10.247
find out what you can about her.

36:10.383 --> 36:11.415
[Joaquin] Copy that.

36:11.552 --> 36:12.995
I'll call you back later.

36:43.992 --> 36:45.525
[Sidewinder]
Target eliminated.

36:45.928 --> 36:47.860
Stand by for proof of death.

36:47.995 --> 36:49.434
[sirens wailing]

36:49.569 --> 36:51.170
[tires screech]

36:51.672 --> 36:52.910
Hmm.

36:55.415 --> 36:56.477
[grunts]

37:00.922 --> 37:02.688
[both grunting]

37:04.731 --> 37:05.969
[groans]

37:12.175 --> 37:13.245
[panting]

37:13.381 --> 37:15.014
No way you came
all the way from Mexico

37:15.150 --> 37:16.416
just to blow up my car.

37:16.552 --> 37:18.995
So you must have made up
with the buyer.

37:19.397 --> 37:20.322
[grunts]

37:20.457 --> 37:21.657
Get him on the phone.

37:21.794 --> 37:23.469
Let me see
if I can resolve this.

37:23.604 --> 37:25.866
"Resolve this"?

37:27.771 --> 37:29.471
The buyer told me everything.

37:30.108 --> 37:33.651
He mentioned that if you
survived the grenade,

37:33.787 --> 37:40.070
there was a 77% chance
you'd try to talk me down.

37:40.571 --> 37:41.439
Hmm.

37:41.575 --> 37:42.901
Look at that.

37:43.270 --> 37:44.738
[gunshot]

37:50.482 --> 37:51.389
[Sam grunts]

37:54.324 --> 37:55.826
[grunts]

38:00.677 --> 38:01.772
[grunts]

38:06.021 --> 38:07.454
[bullets clattering]

38:14.898 --> 38:17.175
The buyer told me
a lot actually.

38:17.310 --> 38:19.147
After he didn't show in Mexico,

38:19.283 --> 38:21.715
he agreed to pay me double
to take you out.

38:21.851 --> 38:26.788
What he doesn't know is that
I would kill you for free.

38:27.192 --> 38:32.141
How often do you get a chance
to kill Captain America?

38:34.570 --> 38:35.807
[sizzles]

38:43.758 --> 38:46.059
You're desperate
without your gear.

38:46.461 --> 38:47.501
[grunts]

38:49.842 --> 38:51.169
[wheezing]

38:51.471 --> 38:52.781
Nope.

38:52.916 --> 38:54.343
Just a little meaner.

38:54.478 --> 38:55.844
[wheezing]

38:55.979 --> 38:57.950
- [grunts]
- [phone rings]

39:02.900 --> 39:03.837
Hello.

39:03.972 --> 39:05.373
[voice] Well done, Captain.

39:05.508 --> 39:07.843
But you're not going to like
what's coming next.

39:07.978 --> 39:09.314
[Sam] Who is this?

39:09.883 --> 39:11.186
[phone beeps]

39:17.290 --> 39:19.565
[Indian Prime Minister]
How can we trust you to lead

39:19.700 --> 39:23.309
when you can't even keep
your own house in order?

39:24.577 --> 39:26.782
We have the shooters in custody.

39:27.252 --> 39:29.622
All I'm asking for is patience.

39:29.757 --> 39:31.121
Patience?

39:31.257 --> 39:33.152
From the Hulk Hunter?

39:34.264 --> 39:35.866
That was a long time ago.

39:36.002 --> 39:37.601
Well, Mr. President,

39:37.736 --> 39:41.312
I was almost killed
in your home yesterday.

39:41.447 --> 39:44.749
And today, you are still
locked in your bunker.

39:44.884 --> 39:48.449
You are not in a position
to be asking for anything.

39:48.585 --> 39:49.791
I agree.

39:49.926 --> 39:52.096
We should continue this
conversation another time.

39:52.232 --> 39:54.262
[Ross] Gentlemen, wait.

39:54.399 --> 39:55.404
Please.

39:55.940 --> 39:59.146
This treaty is too important
to let it fall apart now.

39:59.282 --> 40:01.944
We made a promise to our people.

40:02.080 --> 40:04.457
We made a promise to the world.

40:05.521 --> 40:07.154
We must prevail.

40:08.431 --> 40:10.570
We'll need Japan to proceed.

40:10.705 --> 40:13.809
[French President] And
Prime Minister Ozaki's absence

40:13.944 --> 40:15.135
speaks volumes.

40:15.271 --> 40:17.315
I'll get Japan back
to the table.

40:17.452 --> 40:19.820
Ozaki and I go back a long way.

40:20.323 --> 40:22.217
He's running for re-election.

40:22.352 --> 40:25.593
He needs to assert leadership
on this treaty.

40:26.196 --> 40:29.935
All right, Mr. President,
we'll remain patient

40:30.070 --> 40:32.946
while you try
to get Japan on board.

40:33.181 --> 40:34.584
But if you don't,

40:34.719 --> 40:38.392
we'll have to take measures
into our own hands.

40:43.368 --> 40:44.838
I've gotta get out of here.

40:44.973 --> 40:45.931
Sit down.

40:46.067 --> 40:47.543
Sir, the sweep's not complete.

40:48.146 --> 40:50.306
The longer I stay here,

40:50.876 --> 40:52.350
the weaker I look.

40:52.486 --> 40:54.483
[♪ dramatic music playing]

40:54.619 --> 40:55.922
[door opens]

41:02.770 --> 41:04.136
The hell happened to you?

41:05.478 --> 41:07.309
Sidewinder tracked me down.

41:07.445 --> 41:10.049
[scoffs] Well, it looks like
he did a lot more than that.

41:11.050 --> 41:12.625
He's in police custody now.

41:15.191 --> 41:17.068
- Shit, you good?
- I will be.

41:17.204 --> 41:19.298
Last call, trace it.

41:20.505 --> 41:21.544
All right.

41:27.752 --> 41:28.816
Yo, get this.

41:29.285 --> 41:31.056
Ross' advisor, Ruth Bat-Seraph,

41:31.459 --> 41:34.134
she was born in Israel
and trained in the Red Room.

41:34.269 --> 41:35.705
She's ex-Widow.

41:35.842 --> 41:37.503
That basically means
stay the hell out of her way.

41:37.638 --> 41:38.503
Trust me.

41:38.639 --> 41:39.746
Yep.

41:46.461 --> 41:47.627
[Sam] Now, this is weird.

41:47.762 --> 41:51.297
Isaiah had Ross
in his crosshairs.

41:51.733 --> 41:52.866
Couldn't miss.

41:53.002 --> 41:54.501
[Joaquin] I don't get it.

41:54.637 --> 41:56.505
Why go through all that
trouble just to not kill Ross?

41:56.942 --> 41:58.145
I don't know.

41:58.779 --> 41:59.984
Oh, shit.

42:00.120 --> 42:02.050
I think I located
Sidewinder's last caller.

42:02.553 --> 42:04.221
It's in the middle of nowhere,
West Virginia.

42:04.357 --> 42:06.734
It's just, like,
near some forest.

42:06.870 --> 42:08.973
- [Joaquin typing]
- Database only shows one name.

42:09.109 --> 42:11.006
Camp Echo One.

42:12.105 --> 42:13.780
No satellite imagery.

42:14.417 --> 42:16.247
Away from air traffic.

42:17.084 --> 42:19.358
No infrastructure in the area.

42:19.761 --> 42:21.324
- Do you think it's military?
- Yep.

42:21.459 --> 42:23.767
It's a place they send you
and you never leave.

42:26.575 --> 42:30.782
[♪ triumphant music playing]

42:31.486 --> 42:33.321
Ross told me stay out of this.

42:33.958 --> 42:36.518
Eh, he's just the President
of the United States.

42:47.844 --> 42:49.082
[zipper closes]

42:50.953 --> 42:52.686
You don't have to come with me.

42:53.456 --> 42:55.857
Duh, I know.
That's what makes it so noble.

42:55.992 --> 42:57.460
[chuckles]

42:57.595 --> 42:59.133
Pack as much gear
as you can carry.

42:59.269 --> 43:00.974
I don't know when we'll be back.

43:02.011 --> 43:04.577
What, you mean like,
"right now" right now?

43:04.712 --> 43:06.083
Yeah.

43:06.816 --> 43:07.885
Oh, shit. Okay.

43:08.388 --> 43:10.188
Well, it's a long-ass drive
to West Virginia,

43:10.324 --> 43:11.693
so we're gonna need some snacks.

43:11.828 --> 43:13.234
Why did I invite you?

43:13.370 --> 43:15.134
What? Wait, wait, wait.

43:17.903 --> 43:18.944
Wait up!

43:19.347 --> 43:20.506
Ruth Bat-Seraph.

43:20.641 --> 43:22.686
Isaiah Bradley's
in holding cell 14.

43:22.821 --> 43:24.851
- The other shooters are in 15.
- Okay.

43:24.986 --> 43:26.126
Do you need an escort?

43:26.763 --> 43:28.397
- Think I'll be just fine.
- [door buzzes]

43:28.533 --> 43:30.197
- Thanks.
- Yes, ma'am.

43:32.032 --> 43:33.665
[door buzzes]

43:37.785 --> 43:39.320
I'd like to speak to them
one at a time.

43:39.455 --> 43:41.249
Can you... Excuse me?

43:41.384 --> 43:43.861
Payumo.
I'm talking to you. Hey.

43:45.834 --> 43:47.426
- Stop! Drop your weapon!
- [gunshots]

43:47.561 --> 43:49.407
[♪ unsettling music playing]

43:49.542 --> 43:51.536
Payumo, what are you doing?

43:51.938 --> 43:53.375
Drop it.

43:54.648 --> 43:55.544
[gunshot]

43:56.947 --> 43:59.018
[♪ The Fleetwoods "Mr. Blue"
playing over radio]

43:59.154 --> 44:02.459
♪ Call me Mr. Blue ♪

44:03.430 --> 44:09.038
♪ I'm Mr. Blue
Wa-oo-wa-oo ♪

44:09.174 --> 44:10.640
♪ When you say... ♪

44:13.881 --> 44:15.290
[fitness coach on device]
Increase that cadence

44:15.426 --> 44:16.884
and resistance.

44:17.019 --> 44:17.988
Or do whatever the hell
you need to do to get there,

44:18.123 --> 44:19.393
all right?

44:19.762 --> 44:22.764
Just stay in your lane.
Stay in your lane. Here we go.

44:23.200 --> 44:24.369
Out to third!

44:24.506 --> 44:26.012
Eye on the prize.
Eye on the target, baby.

44:26.148 --> 44:28.345
- [sighs] That's enough.
- Don't think about speed now.

44:28.482 --> 44:30.384
Think about direction.
Think about intention.

44:30.854 --> 44:33.020
If Dr. Eccles asks,

44:33.557 --> 44:37.870
you tell her
I did the whole five miles.

44:40.577 --> 44:43.006
That look. [panting]

44:43.375 --> 44:45.886
We touch down in Tokyo at 0600.

44:47.319 --> 44:50.025
You still think
this is a bad idea?

44:50.160 --> 44:51.424
Sir, whoever orchestrated
the attack

44:51.560 --> 44:53.461
on the White House is still
in the wild.

44:53.597 --> 44:55.801
International travel
brings security risks

44:55.937 --> 44:57.131
we can't anticipate.

44:57.902 --> 45:01.043
We barely got Congress
together on this thing.

45:01.580 --> 45:04.351
If we lose
our international partners,

45:04.955 --> 45:06.719
this treaty's toast.

45:08.028 --> 45:09.857
I have to make this work.

45:11.231 --> 45:12.494
Three miles and change.

45:12.631 --> 45:14.569
I'll let Dr. Eccles know.

45:14.939 --> 45:15.907
Five.

45:16.043 --> 45:17.548
- Five.
- Five.

45:17.685 --> 45:19.085
Do we have eyes on Wilson?

45:19.220 --> 45:21.614
He left the base a few hours
ago with Joaquin Torres.

45:21.750 --> 45:22.921
They ditched their smartphones.

45:23.056 --> 45:24.259
They're off-grid.

45:24.394 --> 45:25.961
Well, I don't want a variable
out there

45:26.096 --> 45:27.462
that I can't control.

45:27.598 --> 45:30.035
Get a team,
pick him up, bring him in.

45:30.171 --> 45:31.502
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

45:31.872 --> 45:33.606
[reporter on radio] Breaking
news out of Washington,

45:33.743 --> 45:35.514
President Ross is
on his way to Japan

45:35.650 --> 45:37.684
just a day after surviving
an assassination attempt...

45:37.819 --> 45:40.124
Bet you used to play this
old-ass game all the time.

45:40.260 --> 45:41.189
[exclaims] Damn it.
This is hard.

45:41.324 --> 45:42.759
- [laughs]
- Right.

45:42.895 --> 45:44.365
[reporter on radio]
The high-stakes diplomatic...

45:44.500 --> 45:45.596
[Sam] How far are we
from Camp Echo One?

45:46.166 --> 45:48.470
[reporter on radio] ...over
control of Celestial Island.

45:48.606 --> 45:50.943
We are about, like,
an hour away.

45:51.078 --> 45:51.985
[phone vibrates]

45:56.756 --> 45:59.396
Sam, shit. They just
shot up Isaiah's prison.

45:59.799 --> 46:00.825
Is he okay?

46:00.961 --> 46:03.132
Yeah, Isaiah's good,
but the others,

46:03.268 --> 46:04.265
they're dead.

46:04.400 --> 46:05.737
Shit.

46:06.373 --> 46:07.907
Should we go back?

46:10.016 --> 46:11.082
No.

46:11.218 --> 46:12.753
We keep going.

46:12.890 --> 46:14.924
The buyer is pretty smart,
but we're not taking the bait.

46:15.060 --> 46:18.230
Only way to help Isaiah is to
figure out who's behind this.

46:18.366 --> 46:19.936
And whoever is behind it,

46:20.438 --> 46:22.639
they do not want
us getting closer.

46:24.475 --> 46:27.517
[phone vibrating]

46:28.217 --> 46:29.183
Cooper.

46:29.518 --> 46:30.987
What's happening?

46:31.122 --> 46:33.327
[Cooper] Mr. President,
as a precautionary measure,

46:33.463 --> 46:34.998
I have moved the prisoner to...

46:35.133 --> 46:36.132
[gunshot]

46:36.835 --> 46:41.206
President Ross,
I miss our little visits.

46:41.575 --> 46:42.643
Tell me something.

46:42.778 --> 46:45.184
Do you ever stop to ask yourself

46:45.320 --> 46:46.889
who's playing the music?

46:47.025 --> 46:48.427
It's you.

46:48.896 --> 46:50.261
The White House,

46:50.397 --> 46:51.660
the assassination attempt.

46:51.795 --> 46:53.667
That's a way of putting it.

46:53.803 --> 46:56.771
[Ross] I helped you more
than anyone else.

46:56.906 --> 46:58.474
[voice]
Only to get what you want.

46:58.610 --> 46:59.577
[Ross] What do you want?

46:59.713 --> 47:01.484
[voice] I wanted my life back,

47:01.620 --> 47:03.285
but it's too late for that now.

47:03.421 --> 47:04.556
You've gotta...

47:04.692 --> 47:06.559
You gotta understand
my position.

47:06.694 --> 47:08.769
- I...
- [voice] Oh, I do.

47:09.139 --> 47:12.034
You let me rot in this prison.

47:12.170 --> 47:14.606
And it was my curse
to watch your betrayal

47:14.742 --> 47:16.780
written in probabilities.

47:17.617 --> 47:20.419
I'm making my own choices now.

47:20.555 --> 47:23.027
So many surprises left.

47:23.164 --> 47:24.300
When I'm done,

47:24.435 --> 47:26.931
everyone will know
just who you are,

47:27.066 --> 47:30.511
and Betty will despise you
even more.

47:31.181 --> 47:32.680
Goodbye, Mr. President.

47:36.226 --> 47:37.386
[Isaiah] The hell is going on?

47:37.788 --> 47:39.631
I'm putting you in solitary.

47:39.766 --> 47:40.693
Yeah.

47:41.062 --> 47:43.401
Nobody's gonna put me
in solitary ever again.

47:43.537 --> 47:45.042
It's for your own protection.

47:45.679 --> 47:48.611
I'll tell you this one more
time for your protection,

47:48.747 --> 47:51.480
I ain't goin'
in a box ever again.

47:52.250 --> 47:54.656
I won't be able to
guarantee your safety.

47:54.792 --> 47:56.992
Safety ain't all
it's cracked up to be.

47:58.332 --> 47:59.600
You still think

47:59.736 --> 48:00.835
I had somethin'
to do with all of this?

48:01.603 --> 48:02.469
I don't know.

48:02.604 --> 48:03.940
[phone vibrates]

48:08.991 --> 48:10.184
Mr. President.

48:10.320 --> 48:11.525
[Ross] I need you
to drop whatever you're doin'.

48:11.660 --> 48:13.324
Camp Echo One's
been compromised.

48:13.793 --> 48:15.370
Yes, Mr. President.

48:43.058 --> 48:44.086
This is it.

48:44.722 --> 48:45.757
Camp Echo One.

48:45.892 --> 48:47.861
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

48:47.997 --> 48:50.404
[Sam]
Telescopes must be a facade.

48:50.540 --> 48:52.410
We gotta see what's underneath.

48:55.914 --> 48:57.817
[Sam]
We've got cameras and guards.

48:57.953 --> 49:00.625
Redwing, cut the fence
and go loop the feed.

49:05.463 --> 49:08.835
Yeah, we got a 28-second
window to get past the guards.

49:08.971 --> 49:10.975
We gotta do the door manually.

49:12.678 --> 49:15.115
Three, two, one,

49:15.517 --> 49:16.591
go.

49:25.405 --> 49:26.710
[grunts]

49:30.284 --> 49:31.520
15 seconds.

49:31.657 --> 49:32.920
- I'm trying, man!
- [electricity crackles]

49:33.621 --> 49:34.891
[Joaquin] Shit!

49:35.999 --> 49:37.093
[Sam grunts]

49:39.269 --> 49:40.969
[both grunting]

49:47.716 --> 49:49.491
[doors clang]

49:52.497 --> 49:53.929
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

50:08.195 --> 50:10.159
[lights buzzing]

50:22.219 --> 50:23.956
[Joaquin]
There's no prisoners in here.

50:41.822 --> 50:45.834
[door clanking]

51:12.626 --> 51:15.124
[Sam] Why is there a lab
in this prison?

51:23.006 --> 51:24.813
What the hell is this place?

52:37.462 --> 52:39.027
[Sam] What the hell?

52:45.840 --> 52:46.773
[Ross] Ozaki-san,

52:46.909 --> 52:48.344
I want to assure you

52:48.481 --> 52:51.587
America remains committed
to sharing our adamantium...

52:51.723 --> 52:53.516
...with the rest of the world.

52:53.652 --> 52:57.155
I trust Japan shares
that commitment.

52:57.558 --> 52:59.728
The world needs this treaty.

53:02.844 --> 53:04.980
Diplomacy must be hard for you.

53:05.616 --> 53:07.018
A man in a country

53:07.153 --> 53:09.924
so used to taking
whatever he wants by force.

53:10.426 --> 53:11.819
Excuse me?

53:11.954 --> 53:14.095
How else to explain your theft
of our adamantium,

53:14.230 --> 53:17.496
only to return it to us
in Washington.

53:17.899 --> 53:20.840
What you're accusing us of
is baseless

53:20.976 --> 53:22.973
and insulting.

53:23.109 --> 53:26.753
So, the information
my intelligence team received

53:26.888 --> 53:28.360
and verified

53:28.496 --> 53:30.294
is incorrect?

53:35.366 --> 53:36.769
[chuckles] Wh...

53:40.453 --> 53:41.878
[Ross sighs]

53:42.623 --> 53:43.816
I'm a fool.

53:45.558 --> 53:49.068
I'm a fool to negotiate
with someone so naive

53:49.203 --> 53:51.975
they don't realize
they're being played.

53:52.642 --> 53:53.869
Naive?

53:54.980 --> 53:56.818
If I'd stolen the sample,

53:57.220 --> 54:01.025
why would I order Captain
America to retrieve it?

54:01.161 --> 54:04.164
I suppose
we'll never know the truth.

54:09.841 --> 54:13.316
Whatever game you're playing,
Japan wants no part in it.

54:13.953 --> 54:15.880
Don't test us, Mr. President.

54:22.997 --> 54:25.364
He's got optogenetic data
on a lot of people.

54:25.935 --> 54:27.574
Don't make me look up words,
Joaquin.

54:27.709 --> 54:29.605
I think he's figured out a way
to plant commands

54:29.741 --> 54:30.683
into people's subconscious

54:30.820 --> 54:32.351
using flashes of light.

54:32.754 --> 54:35.560
This "Mr. Blue" song seems
to be some kind of trigger.

54:35.696 --> 54:36.988
Mind control.

54:37.566 --> 54:38.491
Yeah.

54:38.626 --> 54:40.368
That explains Isaiah.

54:46.247 --> 54:48.418
And that's more important.

54:48.820 --> 54:49.821
Take risks.

54:50.325 --> 54:52.687
Use those incredible brains
of yours.

54:52.823 --> 54:55.134
[Sterns] Wasn't
half bad-looking, was I?

55:01.441 --> 55:03.007
[Sam] Samuel Sterns.

55:05.721 --> 55:08.560
[Sterns] You know, it takes
an awful lot to surprise me.

55:08.696 --> 55:10.493
[door buzzes]

55:10.629 --> 55:13.971
There was an 89% chance
you'd turn around

55:14.107 --> 55:17.106
if I put Isaiah Bradley at risk,

55:17.242 --> 55:19.380
yet here you stand.

55:20.786 --> 55:21.784
You're the buyer.

55:21.919 --> 55:23.023
[Sterns] Indeed.

55:23.158 --> 55:25.327
Hiring SERPENT was
a necessary step

55:25.462 --> 55:28.465
to create a chain
of statistical certainties.

55:28.600 --> 55:30.897
Maybe you're not as smart
as you think you are.

55:31.565 --> 55:33.408
I am, actually.

55:33.543 --> 55:36.617
My mind sees it all,
every probable outcome.

55:37.287 --> 55:40.157
So you hire SERPENT
to steal the adamantium,

55:40.292 --> 55:42.492
shoot up Ross' summit
announcing it

55:42.627 --> 55:45.124
and now you're just
sitting here, waiting.

55:45.860 --> 55:47.394
Why do you wanna kill Ross?

55:47.530 --> 55:51.443
[Sterns] Why does everyone
think that I wanna kill Ross?

55:51.812 --> 55:55.948
Is it because he imprisoned me
here without a trial

55:56.083 --> 55:58.792
after an infusion of gamma
warped the structure

55:58.927 --> 56:00.154
of my brain?

56:04.002 --> 56:05.539
Damn.

56:05.674 --> 56:08.606
[Sterns] Once Ross discovered
how useful I could be,

56:08.742 --> 56:11.515
he kept me here for 16 years,

56:11.651 --> 56:14.524
turning my mind
to solving his problems.

56:14.826 --> 56:18.630
My solutions brought him the
highest office in the country.

56:20.129 --> 56:23.609
If I wanted Ross dead,
he'd be dead.

56:24.145 --> 56:25.477
Well, whatever you're doing,

56:25.846 --> 56:28.685
you're hurting a lot of
people, including my friend.

56:28.821 --> 56:31.718
So this is the last chance
I'm gonna give you to stop it.

56:31.853 --> 56:33.791
Why are you protecting him?

56:34.093 --> 56:36.602
Ross knows I'm responsible
for the White House,

56:36.737 --> 56:39.767
yet he's still letting Isaiah
sit in prison for it.

56:39.902 --> 56:41.436
You know he'll never change.

56:41.905 --> 56:42.982
Let me finish my work.

56:43.117 --> 56:44.416
I'm afraid I can't do that.

56:44.551 --> 56:47.016
- [device whirring]
- [Sam grunting]

56:48.520 --> 56:49.862
[groans]

56:49.998 --> 56:53.160
Please don't be boring!

56:54.598 --> 56:55.572
[grunts]

57:00.383 --> 57:01.953
You think they'll stop us?

57:02.089 --> 57:03.319
[Sterns] For long enough.

57:03.456 --> 57:05.383
You're a fascinating problem.

57:06.087 --> 57:08.331
But soon
you'll be off the board,

57:08.467 --> 57:10.670
so you don't surprise me again.

57:11.740 --> 57:13.902
This is messed up, man.
It's not even their choice.

57:14.037 --> 57:16.041
I know.
Just try and neutralize.

57:17.018 --> 57:19.179
[all grunting]

57:28.072 --> 57:29.673
[yelling]

57:50.886 --> 57:52.018
[groans]

57:52.154 --> 57:54.657
[Sam grunting]

58:20.044 --> 58:21.270
[soldier groans]

58:23.646 --> 58:24.542
[Joaquin] Punk-ass.

58:24.678 --> 58:25.752
[grunts]

58:28.722 --> 58:29.760
[door buzzes]

58:40.150 --> 58:42.279
Stand down!

58:44.083 --> 58:45.685
I'm taking them in.

58:46.055 --> 58:47.663
I'll deal with these two.

58:49.664 --> 58:51.572
[sighs] Okay.

59:14.218 --> 59:15.446
[soldier groans]

59:16.283 --> 59:17.689
What the hell
are you guys doing here?

59:17.825 --> 59:20.257
Well, that's what
I should be asking you.

59:20.626 --> 59:21.621
Where's Sterns?

59:22.926 --> 59:25.304
If Sterns is in the wind,
we need to set a perimeter,

59:25.440 --> 59:26.900
roadblocks, air support.

59:27.037 --> 59:28.277
He can't have gone far.

59:28.413 --> 59:29.612
Why are you helping us?

59:30.115 --> 59:32.680
'Cause you were right.
I thought that was obvious.

59:33.284 --> 59:34.758
- [FBI agent] Freeze!
- Oh. It's okay.

59:34.893 --> 59:36.586
We have orders to take
Captain America into custody.

59:36.721 --> 59:38.660
You already have one
Captain America in custody.

59:38.795 --> 59:39.996
You want another?

59:40.133 --> 59:41.296
You're under arrest
for trespassing

59:41.432 --> 59:43.401
on restricted
government property.

59:44.570 --> 59:45.905
Being right always go like this?

59:46.041 --> 59:47.442
Most of the time.

59:49.681 --> 59:51.987
I have the clearances.
It's been a long day.

59:52.123 --> 59:54.424
She's ex-Widow.
Just zap the guy.

59:54.559 --> 59:56.862
These orders come
from the President himself.

59:56.997 --> 59:58.195
Get them out of here.

59:58.331 --> 59:59.798
Then we'll just call him.

59:59.933 --> 01:00:01.101
[♪ The Fleetwoods "Mr. Blue"
playing over radio]

01:00:01.237 --> 01:00:02.503
Ruth, uncuff us now!

01:00:02.639 --> 01:00:04.482
♪ I'm Mr. Blue
Wa-oo-wa-oo ♪

01:00:04.618 --> 01:00:06.049
♪ When you say... ♪

01:00:06.186 --> 01:00:07.348
Oh, shit, shit, shit, shit.
Not again.

01:00:07.484 --> 01:00:09.695
- Run!
- [Ruth] Go, go, go. Come on.

01:00:11.022 --> 01:00:12.195
[grunts]

01:00:17.674 --> 01:00:18.344
[Sam] Go!

01:00:18.479 --> 01:00:21.146
[bullets ricochet]

01:00:23.382 --> 01:00:24.415
[senior advisor]
Mr. President,

01:00:24.551 --> 01:00:26.926
Japan's claim seems to be true.

01:00:27.296 --> 01:00:29.762
We're trying to determine
the point of the breach.

01:00:30.366 --> 01:00:32.464
Sir, we have to tell
Ozaki's team something.

01:00:32.600 --> 01:00:33.935
We've got to stop the bleeding.

01:00:34.071 --> 01:00:35.336
I need some time alone.

01:00:35.472 --> 01:00:37.082
We don't have much time, sir.

01:00:37.218 --> 01:00:39.983
Ozaki just decided to advance
his navy on Celestial Island.

01:00:40.519 --> 01:00:42.359
He intends to secure
the adamantium for himself.

01:00:42.495 --> 01:00:44.029
[senior advisor] Jesus.

01:00:44.165 --> 01:00:45.924
France and India are drawing
up occupation strategies...

01:00:46.059 --> 01:00:47.669
Mr. President, I suggest that
we return to DC immediately.

01:00:47.804 --> 01:00:49.402
- No, I disagree.
- Immediately.

01:00:49.537 --> 01:00:50.999
We are going to lose
our opportunity with Ozaki.

01:00:51.135 --> 01:00:52.505
We need to regroup and figure
out a different solution.

01:00:52.641 --> 01:00:54.145
We can't do that.
No, absolutely not!

01:00:54.280 --> 01:00:55.241
We need to ask
for another meeting, sir.

01:00:55.378 --> 01:00:56.546
If we call on Ozaki now,

01:00:56.682 --> 01:00:58.284
and try to reach out to him,
we can...

01:00:58.421 --> 01:00:59.990
We're not gonna miss
the argument.

01:01:00.125 --> 01:01:01.598
We have to have another meeting!

01:01:01.734 --> 01:01:03.495
- [advisors arguing]
- [yells]

01:01:08.677 --> 01:01:12.149
[panting]

01:01:15.084 --> 01:01:20.195
I want Carrier Strike Group
Five deployed immediately.

01:01:20.330 --> 01:01:21.763
Tell 'em
I'm on my way there now.

01:01:21.899 --> 01:01:24.444
Sir, are we seriously
talking about taking control

01:01:24.579 --> 01:01:25.713
of Japan's adamantium?

01:01:25.849 --> 01:01:28.380
I'm not going home empty-handed.

01:01:28.517 --> 01:01:31.985
If only one country is going
to control adamantium,

01:01:32.121 --> 01:01:33.896
it's going to be us.

01:01:38.804 --> 01:01:40.701
Make the call!

01:01:43.316 --> 01:01:44.611
Taylor!

01:01:44.746 --> 01:01:46.117
[senior advisor]
The President has informed me

01:01:46.253 --> 01:01:47.382
that we need to move
Strike Group Five

01:01:47.519 --> 01:01:49.083
to Celestial Island immediately.

01:01:49.218 --> 01:01:52.560
I want to be en route to the
Indian Ocean within the hour.

01:01:52.695 --> 01:01:56.568
Mr. President,
this is extremely dangerous.

01:01:57.336 --> 01:01:58.334
If a war breaks out...

01:01:58.470 --> 01:02:00.344
I was a wartime general.

01:02:01.081 --> 01:02:03.482
Now I'm a wartime president.

01:02:06.222 --> 01:02:07.931
Yes, sir, Mr. President.

01:02:32.175 --> 01:02:33.509
What are we doing here?

01:02:33.644 --> 01:02:35.584
You say Ross' orders was
to take us into custody

01:02:35.721 --> 01:02:37.716
so I called in a favor.

01:02:38.352 --> 01:02:39.754
Thanks for doing this.

01:02:39.889 --> 01:02:42.195
No problem, Cap. Brass never
makes it down here.

01:02:42.330 --> 01:02:44.031
Terminal's set up, ready to go.

01:02:44.734 --> 01:02:46.742
You sure you can knock out
Sterns' mind control?

01:02:46.877 --> 01:02:48.238
I should be able
to run a program

01:02:48.374 --> 01:02:49.807
that blocks the light signals

01:02:49.943 --> 01:02:52.182
that Sterns has been
sending out to control people.

01:02:52.318 --> 01:02:54.617
What if
he's already gotten someone?

01:02:55.353 --> 01:02:56.720
That's a good point.

01:02:59.699 --> 01:03:00.898
[♪ The Fleetwoods "Mr. Blue"
playing over speakers]

01:03:01.034 --> 01:03:02.202
Are you crazy?

01:03:02.338 --> 01:03:04.737
♪ I'm Mr. Blue
Wa-oo-wa-oo ♪

01:03:04.873 --> 01:03:09.214
♪ When you say you love me
Oh, Mr. Blue ♪

01:03:09.349 --> 01:03:10.448
We're clear here, at least.

01:03:10.583 --> 01:03:12.083
You have anybody that you trust

01:03:12.219 --> 01:03:14.222
that can take a look at these
and tell me what's in 'em?

01:03:14.358 --> 01:03:15.828
Sure, I got someone.

01:03:15.964 --> 01:03:17.001
I'll get on it.

01:03:17.137 --> 01:03:19.370
- Thanks. Our guy here?
- Through there.

01:03:20.137 --> 01:03:21.374
Listen in.

01:03:25.011 --> 01:03:27.518
[Sidewinder] I'm amazed
you're still standing.

01:03:27.653 --> 01:03:30.826
Most men don't survive
an axe to the gut.

01:03:30.963 --> 01:03:32.291
Kevlar weave, I presume?

01:03:32.426 --> 01:03:33.592
Perks of the job.

01:03:34.362 --> 01:03:37.333
You said you were gonna find
the man who wasted your time.

01:03:37.736 --> 01:03:39.040
I wanna know what you learned.

01:03:39.176 --> 01:03:40.277
Samuel Sterns.

01:03:40.412 --> 01:03:42.310
Gruesome fella, don't you think?

01:03:42.445 --> 01:03:44.019
I've seen worse.

01:03:44.155 --> 01:03:45.248
Not without your Avengers.

01:03:45.384 --> 01:03:46.622
[scoffs]

01:03:47.425 --> 01:03:48.962
Full immunity and I'll talk.

01:03:49.098 --> 01:03:50.194
[scoffs] You're crazy.

01:03:50.329 --> 01:03:51.699
Who you kiddin'?

01:03:51.834 --> 01:03:53.240
You're here because
you're all out of options.

01:03:53.375 --> 01:03:54.768
You heard
what he did to those shooters.

01:03:55.138 --> 01:03:57.778
A guy like Sterns doesn't like
loose ends alive.

01:03:57.914 --> 01:03:58.975
[sighs]

01:03:59.112 --> 01:04:02.951
Reduced sentence,
Allenwood, my own cell.

01:04:03.722 --> 01:04:05.462
Lemme hear what you got first.

01:04:07.833 --> 01:04:10.632
You know, it was my old unit
that found Sterns

01:04:10.768 --> 01:04:12.009
in the wreckage of Harlem.

01:04:12.713 --> 01:04:14.940
They said he'd been infected
with Bruce Banner's blood,

01:04:15.076 --> 01:04:16.952
but it didn't give him strength.

01:04:17.087 --> 01:04:18.355
What did it give him?

01:04:18.491 --> 01:04:21.362
A mind capable
of impossible calculations.

01:04:21.996 --> 01:04:23.592
Ross being Ross,

01:04:23.727 --> 01:04:25.236
he saw an opportunity.

01:04:25.639 --> 01:04:28.502
Instead of removing the gamma
from Sterns' blood,

01:04:28.637 --> 01:04:31.045
he upped the dose.

01:04:31.649 --> 01:04:34.650
Made Sterns his own
personal think tank,

01:04:35.052 --> 01:04:38.390
creating technology
and weapons for the state.

01:04:38.792 --> 01:04:40.867
- Holy shit.
- [chuckles]

01:04:41.304 --> 01:04:42.697
Why did Sterns go along with it?

01:04:42.832 --> 01:04:45.441
Camp Echo One was the stick.

01:04:45.576 --> 01:04:48.614
I imagine
a pardon was the carrot.

01:04:50.283 --> 01:04:54.423
Ross told Sterns he'd let him
go once he became president.

01:04:54.558 --> 01:04:57.125
And yet, here we are.

01:04:59.034 --> 01:05:02.641
So Sterns hired you
to steal Japan's adamantium

01:05:02.777 --> 01:05:05.075
knowing it would divide
the two countries.

01:05:07.654 --> 01:05:09.853
He paid us
through a CIA black fund.

01:05:09.989 --> 01:05:12.724
That could kill the treaty
and start a war.

01:05:13.093 --> 01:05:15.598
And Ross would be blamed
for the chaos.

01:05:16.101 --> 01:05:18.409
How do you think a man
with Ross' temperament

01:05:18.545 --> 01:05:21.845
will deal with being caught
in a trap?

01:05:22.983 --> 01:05:26.354
If you break out of Allenwood,
I'll find you.

01:05:26.491 --> 01:05:29.425
When I break out, Captain,

01:05:29.794 --> 01:05:31.898
you won't walk away alive.

01:05:33.539 --> 01:05:34.869
- Did you know?
- Of course not.

01:05:35.004 --> 01:05:37.007
But Ross is not
that man anymore.

01:05:37.142 --> 01:05:39.485
None of us have to be
defined by our past.

01:05:39.620 --> 01:05:42.287
Cap, my guy needs 24 hours
on the pills.

01:05:42.423 --> 01:05:43.590
Okay. We need to get to DC

01:05:43.726 --> 01:05:45.493
and tell Ross
what Sterns is planning.

01:05:45.628 --> 01:05:47.128
President Ross isn't in DC.

01:05:47.532 --> 01:05:48.864
He's on the USS Milius.

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:50.738
They just moved
into the Indian Ocean.

01:05:50.873 --> 01:05:52.772
Japan's warships are also
in proximity.

01:05:52.907 --> 01:05:55.583
Shit. Suit up.
We need to move.

01:05:58.089 --> 01:05:59.150
[doorbell rings]

01:06:02.229 --> 01:06:03.162
May I help you?

01:06:03.297 --> 01:06:04.364
Hello, Admiral.

01:06:04.499 --> 01:06:06.033
May I use your phone?

01:06:06.168 --> 01:06:08.175
[family member] Hey, honey.
Who's at the door?

01:06:08.311 --> 01:06:10.480
- [gunshots]
- [screams]

01:06:13.220 --> 01:06:14.450
[Joaquin] Holy shit.

01:06:14.854 --> 01:06:16.453
You ever see anything like this?

01:06:16.590 --> 01:06:17.723
[Sam] No, I haven't.

01:06:17.858 --> 01:06:19.190
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

01:06:44.278 --> 01:06:46.112
[Ruth] Let me do the talking
or he'll never listen.

01:06:46.247 --> 01:06:48.518
I haven't seen Ross like this
since the army.

01:06:48.654 --> 01:06:50.188
He better snap out of it.

01:06:50.324 --> 01:06:52.994
Because whatever Sterns is
planning, it's happening soon.

01:06:54.330 --> 01:06:56.837
[Ross] I want a fleet of F-18s
ready to catapult.

01:06:56.972 --> 01:06:59.512
If they turn that ship around,
I want...

01:07:00.843 --> 01:07:02.010
What's he doing here?

01:07:02.146 --> 01:07:04.219
I told you not
to get involved, Wilson.

01:07:04.355 --> 01:07:05.421
I brought him, sir.

01:07:05.557 --> 01:07:06.824
[Ross] I want him outta here!

01:07:06.960 --> 01:07:08.454
Sir, you asked me
to run this investigation,

01:07:08.589 --> 01:07:11.666
- and the situation is...
- Don't bother with excuses.

01:07:11.803 --> 01:07:14.238
You had a simple job
and you failed.

01:07:14.374 --> 01:07:15.403
Mr. President,

01:07:16.241 --> 01:07:18.714
we've uncovered intel
at Camp Echo One

01:07:18.851 --> 01:07:21.214
that could put millions
of lives at risk.

01:07:21.350 --> 01:07:23.827
Now, you and I both know
Isaiah's innocent.

01:07:24.831 --> 01:07:27.363
I'm happy to have
this conversation in public,

01:07:27.498 --> 01:07:28.735
if you like.

01:07:35.919 --> 01:07:38.150
[Jackal] This is crazy.
Japan's supposed to be our...

01:07:38.286 --> 01:07:40.555
- [radio feedback squeals]
- [Whiskey] Jackal?

01:07:40.691 --> 01:07:42.160
Jackal, do you copy?

01:07:42.295 --> 01:07:43.297
[♪ The Fleetwoods "Mr. Blue"
playing over radio]

01:07:43.432 --> 01:07:45.868
♪ I'm Mr. Blue ♪

01:07:47.639 --> 01:07:49.205
Make it quick, Wilson.

01:07:50.781 --> 01:07:52.674
I've got Japan's fleet on my ass

01:07:52.809 --> 01:07:54.684
trying to make it to
that island before we do.

01:07:54.820 --> 01:07:56.253
That's exactly what he wants.

01:07:56.388 --> 01:07:59.058
Sterns has been pulling
the strings on everything.

01:07:59.193 --> 01:08:00.994
SERPENT's theft
of the adamantium,

01:08:01.130 --> 01:08:02.666
the attack on the White House.

01:08:02.801 --> 01:08:04.603
The CIA leak to Japan.

01:08:05.340 --> 01:08:07.547
He's pitting you and Japan
against each other

01:08:07.683 --> 01:08:09.344
to ensure that
this moment happens.

01:08:09.480 --> 01:08:11.687
How the hell did he do
all that from prison?

01:08:11.823 --> 01:08:14.792
Mind control.
He created a technology

01:08:14.928 --> 01:08:16.496
that allowed him
to control the minds

01:08:16.631 --> 01:08:18.235
of anyone he targeted.

01:08:18.504 --> 01:08:19.898
Including maybe you, sir.

01:08:20.034 --> 01:08:22.304
[♪ tense music playing]

01:08:25.809 --> 01:08:28.217
Have you been feelin'
like yourself lately?

01:08:34.534 --> 01:08:35.867
Of course I have.

01:08:36.002 --> 01:08:38.097
But he has
your data, sir. Why?

01:08:38.234 --> 01:08:39.302
I don't know.

01:08:39.871 --> 01:08:43.250
If he can control minds,
surely he can hack files.

01:08:43.386 --> 01:08:46.319
The logs show that you visited
Camp Echo One numerous times.

01:08:46.454 --> 01:08:50.961
To ensure a high-value
prisoner was secure.

01:08:51.097 --> 01:08:52.297
Yeah, but the scans, the EKG,

01:08:52.432 --> 01:08:54.406
the blood work
was all taken there, sir.

01:08:54.542 --> 01:08:55.709
This is ridiculous.

01:08:55.845 --> 01:08:57.304
Mr. President,
answer the question.

01:08:57.439 --> 01:08:59.449
I don't have to answer you!

01:08:59.585 --> 01:09:00.886
Why visit a Black Site,

01:09:01.021 --> 01:09:02.488
- in the middle of nowhere...
- Wilson, stop!

01:09:02.624 --> 01:09:04.058
I order you to stop!

01:09:04.194 --> 01:09:05.453
- ...to conduct these tests?
- I order you to stop!

01:09:05.589 --> 01:09:07.695
- Why?
- Because I was dying,

01:09:07.830 --> 01:09:08.898
goddamn it!

01:09:09.034 --> 01:09:11.038
[♪ tense music continues]

01:09:13.505 --> 01:09:16.412
Because my heart was failing!

01:09:18.088 --> 01:09:20.684
No one could figure it out
until he did.

01:09:25.101 --> 01:09:28.733
These things have kept me alive.

01:09:29.680 --> 01:09:32.441
And in return, I gave him hope

01:09:32.577 --> 01:09:34.712
that he might get his life back.

01:09:35.658 --> 01:09:39.087
He got a lab to do the work.

01:09:39.724 --> 01:09:41.693
I even tried
to get him moved but...

01:09:41.828 --> 01:09:43.840
But you couldn't risk
losing the pills.

01:09:49.349 --> 01:09:52.088
After your friend the Hulk
and the Abomination

01:09:52.223 --> 01:09:56.328
destroyed Harlem,
someone had to take the fall.

01:09:56.731 --> 01:09:58.165
Sterns was just...

01:09:58.900 --> 01:10:00.940
collateral damage.

01:10:04.177 --> 01:10:06.985
I have dedicated my entire life

01:10:07.721 --> 01:10:09.782
to serving this country.

01:10:13.559 --> 01:10:15.794
The one person that matters...

01:10:16.971 --> 01:10:19.367
doesn't seem to understand.

01:10:20.204 --> 01:10:26.992
Betty never forgave me for
sending the army after Banner.

01:10:29.522 --> 01:10:31.727
I had to survive...

01:10:36.404 --> 01:10:38.739
so that my daughter knew

01:10:38.874 --> 01:10:41.420
that there was more
to her father.

01:10:42.257 --> 01:10:44.154
That I'm the same man
that used to take her

01:10:44.289 --> 01:10:46.261
to see the cherry blossoms.

01:10:47.933 --> 01:10:50.071
She still can, sir.

01:10:52.436 --> 01:10:54.112
I know what it's like...

01:10:56.184 --> 01:10:58.715
to feel you have
somethin' to prove.

01:10:59.916 --> 01:11:02.194
Everyone only seeing one thing.

01:11:03.826 --> 01:11:06.195
But when showing
there's more to you,

01:11:06.832 --> 01:11:09.232
it's not about
when times are easy.

01:11:09.803 --> 01:11:12.511
It's about moments like this.

01:11:14.386 --> 01:11:17.321
Now, we're here
because Sterns wants revenge

01:11:17.457 --> 01:11:19.865
and doesn't care
if he incites a war.

01:11:20.000 --> 01:11:22.459
We're playing right
into his hand.

01:11:22.862 --> 01:11:24.798
Mr. President,
two of our F-18s

01:11:24.934 --> 01:11:27.076
just fired
on the Japanese fleet.

01:11:27.211 --> 01:11:28.973
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

01:11:30.077 --> 01:11:32.313
[male commander]
Keep hailing those pilots.

01:11:33.117 --> 01:11:35.585
[male specialist] Damage
to Japanese fleet minimal.

01:11:36.056 --> 01:11:37.495
[male commander]
Ready air defense systems.

01:11:37.630 --> 01:11:39.768
[Ross] What the hell
are those pilots doing?

01:11:39.904 --> 01:11:40.939
Call them back in.

01:11:41.074 --> 01:11:42.206
[male commander]
We tried, sir.

01:11:42.342 --> 01:11:43.703
Jackal and Whiskey
won't respond.

01:11:43.839 --> 01:11:45.377
We gotta get our birds
in the air.

01:11:45.512 --> 01:11:47.643
You have two ready
to fly now, sir.

01:11:47.779 --> 01:11:49.222
[♪ dramatic music playing]

01:11:49.558 --> 01:11:50.455
Go.

01:11:57.370 --> 01:11:59.969
[♪ dramatic music continues]

01:12:05.321 --> 01:12:06.714
[Joaquin]
Sterns got to our pilots

01:12:06.850 --> 01:12:08.288
before I shut down the system.

01:12:08.958 --> 01:12:10.488
[Captain America]
We need to get the Japanese

01:12:10.623 --> 01:12:11.658
out of the air.

01:12:12.095 --> 01:12:13.695
Stay close
and don't get yourself killed.

01:12:13.831 --> 01:12:15.538
[Joaquin] No dying, copy that.

01:12:21.614 --> 01:12:23.349
Return to your fleet.

01:12:23.485 --> 01:12:25.360
[in Japanese]

01:12:27.925 --> 01:12:30.436
[Captain America, in Japanese]

01:12:36.711 --> 01:12:38.221
- [gunfire]
- [grunts]

01:12:40.820 --> 01:12:41.993
[Captain America]
Jackal's headed

01:12:42.129 --> 01:12:43.528
towards the Japanese fleet.

01:12:44.793 --> 01:12:46.627
Shit! He just fired on them.

01:12:47.231 --> 01:12:49.442
Mr. President,
do not send more fighters up.

01:12:49.577 --> 01:12:52.348
We need Japan to see
we're trying to deescalate.

01:12:55.417 --> 01:12:57.589
[in Japanese]

01:13:06.711 --> 01:13:09.415
[male specialist] Sir, six
Japanese missiles inbound.

01:13:12.056 --> 01:13:13.555
Launch intercept missiles.

01:13:26.319 --> 01:13:27.913
[Joaquin]
Damn, two got through.

01:13:28.049 --> 01:13:30.148
[Captain America]
Take the one on the right.

01:13:36.335 --> 01:13:38.341
Redwing, a little help.

01:13:57.241 --> 01:14:00.076
Sir, you need to convince
Japan to ground their planes.

01:14:03.724 --> 01:14:05.620
[Prime Minister Ozaki]
This is what we expected

01:14:05.756 --> 01:14:07.256
from a Ross presidency.

01:14:07.392 --> 01:14:10.261
Mr. Prime Minister, two
of our pilots have gone rogue.

01:14:10.396 --> 01:14:12.539
Call off your planes.
We're being manipulated.

01:14:12.675 --> 01:14:13.774
[Prime Minister Ozaki]
Certainly.

01:14:14.176 --> 01:14:15.547
By you.

01:14:15.682 --> 01:14:17.652
Hiding your assassins
behind Captain America.

01:14:18.589 --> 01:14:22.054
He's trying
to bring them down now, sir.

01:14:22.189 --> 01:14:25.124
If those pilots are not
taking orders from you,

01:14:25.260 --> 01:14:28.969
then who gives them
their commands?

01:14:30.343 --> 01:14:31.540
That's what I thought.

01:14:31.675 --> 01:14:32.713
[line disconnects]

01:14:36.181 --> 01:14:37.591
[male commander]
Mr. President?

01:14:38.962 --> 01:14:40.222
[groans]

01:14:41.726 --> 01:14:44.933
[Sterns through earpiece] Ah,
now we're getting somewhere.

01:14:45.068 --> 01:14:48.675
That fire in the belly.
The rage.

01:14:48.811 --> 01:14:50.743
Why don't you just let it out?

01:14:50.879 --> 01:14:52.020
Are you all right, sir?

01:14:52.156 --> 01:14:53.621
[Ross breathes heavily]

01:14:53.757 --> 01:14:56.496
[stammering]
I just need a moment.

01:14:58.059 --> 01:14:59.965
[♪ tense music playing]

01:15:01.709 --> 01:15:04.011
[Captain America] Joaquin,
Whiskey's coming at you.

01:15:04.147 --> 01:15:05.746
[Joaquin] Copy that.

01:15:12.555 --> 01:15:15.928
Sam, once we're done,
you gotta teach me your moves!

01:15:16.063 --> 01:15:18.100
[♪ triumphant music playing]

01:15:22.681 --> 01:15:25.180
[alarm system]
Altitude. Altitude.

01:15:28.721 --> 01:15:29.661
Altitude.

01:15:31.801 --> 01:15:33.427
[Joaquin] Whiskey's away.
Send rescue.

01:15:33.562 --> 01:15:35.267
[male specialist]
Roger, sending rescue.

01:15:35.403 --> 01:15:36.842
You have two Japanese fighters
coming up on your tail.

01:15:36.977 --> 01:15:39.005
[Joaquin] Why the hell
are they still chasing us?

01:15:39.141 --> 01:15:40.442
We're trying to help them.

01:15:40.577 --> 01:15:41.912
[Captain America]
Because Ross won't tell them

01:15:42.048 --> 01:15:43.480
who's really behind this.

01:15:46.323 --> 01:15:48.927
[Sterns] All that hatred
you try to hide,

01:15:49.330 --> 01:15:53.438
all the ugliness,
it's still there, Ross,

01:15:53.841 --> 01:15:56.381
smoldering behind the eyes.

01:15:56.517 --> 01:15:58.752
[♪ dramatic music playing]

01:16:13.115 --> 01:16:15.412
[Captain America] Joaquin,
I'm goin' after Jackal.

01:16:16.748 --> 01:16:19.387
[Joaquin] Roger that.
I'll keep these guys busy.

01:16:24.334 --> 01:16:26.270
What have you done to me,
you bastard?

01:16:26.405 --> 01:16:29.983
[Sterns] What we agreed on.
Maybe a hair more.

01:16:30.352 --> 01:16:31.476
[Ross] You poisoned me!

01:16:31.611 --> 01:16:33.488
[Sterns]
Stop taking the pills then.

01:16:33.623 --> 01:16:35.726
But we both know you won't.

01:16:35.862 --> 01:16:39.968
Give me what I want.
Stop fighting it.

01:16:40.105 --> 01:16:41.263
No!

01:16:41.398 --> 01:16:43.633
[♪ dramatic music continues]

01:17:11.859 --> 01:17:14.563
[Joaquin] Sam, Jackal
just fired his last missiles!

01:17:19.508 --> 01:17:21.314
I got one.
Going after the another.

01:17:21.449 --> 01:17:23.522
- Back off! I'll get it!
- [Joaquin] No, no! I got it.

01:17:23.657 --> 01:17:25.321
- Back off!
- I got it.

01:17:26.086 --> 01:17:27.325
[yells]

01:17:28.531 --> 01:17:29.835
Joaquin!

01:17:37.545 --> 01:17:39.146
Joaquin's down!
I'm goin' after him.

01:17:39.283 --> 01:17:40.389
We'll send search and rescue.

01:17:40.525 --> 01:17:42.390
You have to stop Jackal.

01:17:42.526 --> 01:17:43.421
Damn it!

01:17:43.556 --> 01:17:45.599
I'm putting an end to this now.

01:17:45.735 --> 01:17:47.864
[Sterns] Give in to your rage.

01:17:48.501 --> 01:17:51.536
I'm taking your legacy
as we speak.

01:17:51.672 --> 01:17:54.278
Come on, Ross.
You're almost there.

01:17:54.681 --> 01:17:59.317
You can rip their fleet apart
with your bare hands,

01:17:59.454 --> 01:18:01.360
and kill Captain America.

01:18:04.769 --> 01:18:06.671
[rapid beeping]

01:18:06.806 --> 01:18:07.735
Oh, shit.

01:18:11.650 --> 01:18:12.547
[grunts]

01:18:14.255 --> 01:18:16.896
[Sterns] Let the monster
inside you out.

01:18:18.092 --> 01:18:20.364
[grunting]

01:18:24.805 --> 01:18:27.349
[alarm system]
Altitude, altitude, altitude.

01:18:27.753 --> 01:18:30.719
Altitude, altitude, altitude.

01:18:31.121 --> 01:18:33.087
[Sterns] Unleash your anger.

01:18:33.223 --> 01:18:34.722
Unleash your hatred.

01:18:34.858 --> 01:18:36.661
[Captain America]
Redwing, stabilize!

01:18:41.739 --> 01:18:44.143
[Sterns]
Nothing can stop you, Ross.

01:18:44.279 --> 01:18:46.251
You could crush them all.

01:18:56.469 --> 01:18:58.672
[♪ triumphant music playing]

01:19:01.114 --> 01:19:02.481
[Leila] Mr. President?

01:19:03.855 --> 01:19:05.951
Sir. Are you okay?

01:19:06.086 --> 01:19:08.590
Captain America neutralized
the rogue pilots.

01:19:08.727 --> 01:19:10.865
Japan's recalling their planes.

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:12.497
[Ross pants]

01:19:12.633 --> 01:19:14.367
Get Ozaki back on the line.

01:19:14.503 --> 01:19:16.377
[Ross] We can fix this.

01:19:17.982 --> 01:19:21.354
[hyperventilating]

01:19:21.889 --> 01:19:23.622
[yells]

01:19:24.192 --> 01:19:26.628
[in Japanese]

01:19:30.107 --> 01:19:32.376
[♪ tense music playing]

01:19:34.112 --> 01:19:35.179
Where's Joaquin?

01:19:35.315 --> 01:19:36.953
Med-evac just got to him.

01:19:37.088 --> 01:19:38.586
[Captain America] Thank God.

01:19:46.737 --> 01:19:48.472
[reporter]
A crisis was narrowly avoided

01:19:48.608 --> 01:19:50.245
when a brief dogfight broke out

01:19:50.381 --> 01:19:52.411
between Japanese
and US military forces

01:19:52.546 --> 01:19:54.319
over Celestial Island.

01:19:54.455 --> 01:19:56.356
US Air Force Captain
Joaquin Torres

01:19:56.492 --> 01:19:58.356
was shot down
during the skirmish,

01:19:58.492 --> 01:19:59.860
and is now in surgery at

01:19:59.995 --> 01:20:02.332
Walter Reed National Military
Medical Center.

01:20:02.468 --> 01:20:04.406
His condition is critical.

01:20:04.542 --> 01:20:05.671
[surgeon 1]
Here, give me that clamp.

01:20:05.807 --> 01:20:07.347
[surgeon 2]
Gonna need to pack this!

01:20:08.611 --> 01:20:10.287
[surgeon 2] Suction!

01:20:11.423 --> 01:20:13.524
I can't see anything.
More suction.

01:20:14.126 --> 01:20:15.429
Retractors.

01:20:16.297 --> 01:20:18.534
[footsteps approaching]

01:20:20.107 --> 01:20:21.771
It's a private room.

01:20:23.847 --> 01:20:25.075
Go away.

01:20:31.161 --> 01:20:32.430
I missed you, too.

01:20:38.874 --> 01:20:43.815
I hate to admit it,
I'm glad you're here.

01:20:49.393 --> 01:20:50.464
[sighs]

01:20:50.833 --> 01:20:53.098
You looked good out there
on that six o'clock.

01:20:53.767 --> 01:20:55.576
But then I saw this.

01:20:56.513 --> 01:20:58.911
The doctors had to
restart his heart.

01:21:00.682 --> 01:21:02.325
They don't know if...

01:21:05.230 --> 01:21:06.663
This isn't your fault.

01:21:07.730 --> 01:21:09.735
It makes me think of Steve.

01:21:10.905 --> 01:21:13.976
How many alien invasions
did he stop again?

01:21:14.113 --> 01:21:15.210
Two.

01:21:15.346 --> 01:21:16.245
Two.

01:21:16.381 --> 01:21:17.685
[scoffs]

01:21:18.220 --> 01:21:19.491
Wow.

01:21:21.531 --> 01:21:24.060
What made me think
I could follow that?

01:21:26.873 --> 01:21:31.515
I should've took the serum.
Like Steve, like you.

01:21:33.018 --> 01:21:34.014
Why?

01:21:36.894 --> 01:21:40.698
Because this is all startin'
to seem much bigger than me.

01:21:42.067 --> 01:21:47.211
Ross, he asked me
to restart the Avengers, Buck.

01:21:47.347 --> 01:21:48.877
But Joaquin's in here,

01:21:49.013 --> 01:21:52.251
Isaiah's in prison,
and Sterns...

01:21:53.154 --> 01:21:57.600
I had him. I had Sterns
right in my hands.

01:21:58.466 --> 01:21:59.700
And he got away.

01:22:00.102 --> 01:22:02.538
He damn near pushed us
to the brink of war,

01:22:02.674 --> 01:22:04.416
because I wasn't...

01:22:06.419 --> 01:22:08.148
Say what you need to say.

01:22:13.663 --> 01:22:15.867
Steve made a mistake.

01:22:17.075 --> 01:22:18.272
No, he didn't.

01:22:18.409 --> 01:22:20.309
He gave you that shield

01:22:20.879 --> 01:22:23.117
not because
you're the strongest,

01:22:23.253 --> 01:22:24.720
but because you're you.

01:22:28.697 --> 01:22:30.358
You think if you had that serum

01:22:30.495 --> 01:22:33.268
you'd be able to protect
all the people you care about.

01:22:33.672 --> 01:22:36.242
Steve had it, and he couldn't.

01:22:37.013 --> 01:22:39.816
You're a human being,
and you're doing your best.

01:22:40.854 --> 01:22:42.826
Steve gave people
something to believe in.

01:22:42.961 --> 01:22:43.992
But you...

01:22:44.696 --> 01:22:47.435
you give 'em
something to aspire to.

01:22:50.973 --> 01:22:52.775
Did your speechwriters
help you with that?

01:22:52.911 --> 01:22:54.477
They did, yeah.
The ending, a little bit.

01:22:54.613 --> 01:22:55.780
Well, did you like it?

01:22:55.916 --> 01:22:57.652
No, no, it was good.
Solid B-plus.

01:22:57.788 --> 01:23:00.124
- Emotional.
- Yeah, very. I felt it.

01:23:00.259 --> 01:23:01.290
But just enough.

01:23:01.425 --> 01:23:02.565
Yeah.

01:23:03.765 --> 01:23:05.802
Listen, I gotta catch a plane.

01:23:05.937 --> 01:23:08.874
I have a campaign fundraiser.
It's so stupid.

01:23:13.388 --> 01:23:15.458
It's gonna be all right, man.

01:23:21.368 --> 01:23:22.704
Thanks, Buck.

01:23:23.670 --> 01:23:25.610
I love you, buddy.

01:23:34.760 --> 01:23:36.496
- Was that...
- Yep.

01:23:36.933 --> 01:23:40.707
Future Congressman
James Buchanan Barnes.

01:23:44.376 --> 01:23:47.179
He's taller in real life,
nice smile too,

01:23:47.315 --> 01:23:50.093
good amount of teeth,
great posture.

01:23:50.229 --> 01:23:52.127
He's 110 years old.

01:23:52.596 --> 01:23:53.798
I can work with that.

01:23:53.933 --> 01:23:55.230
[reporter on TV]
While the investigation

01:23:55.365 --> 01:23:56.834
into the White House
assassination attempt

01:23:56.969 --> 01:23:58.369
and the shocking shooting at

01:23:58.504 --> 01:24:01.348
Joint Base Anacostia-Bolling
is still under way,

01:24:01.483 --> 01:24:03.585
Isaiah Bradley is set to go

01:24:03.720 --> 01:24:04.957
before a military judge
tomorrow.

01:24:05.092 --> 01:24:06.286
I need some air.

01:24:06.421 --> 01:24:08.257
[reporter on TV] It's a fall
from grace for a man

01:24:08.392 --> 01:24:11.161
brought out from the shadows
by Captain America.

01:24:11.297 --> 01:24:13.634
Just two years after
being exonerated

01:24:13.770 --> 01:24:15.206
for unjust charges,

01:24:15.342 --> 01:24:18.142
Bradley now finds himself
held in solitary confinement

01:24:18.278 --> 01:24:21.855
and facing a possible
death sentence.

01:24:28.667 --> 01:24:30.201
[phone rings]

01:24:33.276 --> 01:24:35.916
[instructor] Okay, reset.
Let's go again.

01:24:37.750 --> 01:24:39.021
Talk to me.

01:24:39.156 --> 01:24:40.527
[scientist] Dunphy,
you check out my report?

01:24:40.663 --> 01:24:41.657
All right, what am I looking at?

01:24:41.793 --> 01:24:43.258
Those pills you gave me,

01:24:43.394 --> 01:24:44.733
they're loaded
with gamma radiation,

01:24:44.869 --> 01:24:46.836
engineered to be
absorbed into the blood.

01:24:46.973 --> 01:24:48.507
Where the hell
did you get these?

01:24:48.643 --> 01:24:50.681
Shit. I gotta make a call.

01:24:53.279 --> 01:24:55.187
[distorted pulsing sound]

01:24:55.323 --> 01:24:56.994
[groans]

01:24:57.963 --> 01:25:02.234
This sound is currently
affecting your equilibrium.

01:25:02.703 --> 01:25:04.405
When I turn this dial,

01:25:04.874 --> 01:25:07.213
it will disrupt your heartbeat.

01:25:07.849 --> 01:25:10.454
I take no pleasure
in your death,

01:25:10.823 --> 01:25:13.150
but I can't have you
calling the Captain.

01:25:13.285 --> 01:25:16.095
[panting] Who are you?

01:25:16.895 --> 01:25:18.935
Isn't it obvious?

01:25:19.571 --> 01:25:21.232
I'm the hero.

01:25:21.634 --> 01:25:23.945
[distorted pulsing intensifies]

01:25:24.712 --> 01:25:25.748
[muffled scream]

01:25:25.883 --> 01:25:28.085
[♪ unsettling music playing]

01:25:42.418 --> 01:25:43.351
[door opens]

01:25:43.486 --> 01:25:44.888
[Leila] Sir.

01:25:46.761 --> 01:25:48.229
- Agent Taylor.
- [door closes]

01:25:48.631 --> 01:25:49.731
Just wanted to let you know

01:25:49.866 --> 01:25:51.265
that every guest
has been screened,

01:25:51.400 --> 01:25:53.102
and we also did three sweeps
of the Rose Garden.

01:25:53.539 --> 01:25:54.569
Thank you.

01:25:55.273 --> 01:25:57.243
- See you out there.
- Yes, sir.

01:26:00.422 --> 01:26:01.614
[door closes]

01:26:08.800 --> 01:26:10.632
[dial tone]

01:26:16.985 --> 01:26:18.857
- [Betty] Hello?
- [stammers]

01:26:19.426 --> 01:26:21.728
Hello. Hi.

01:26:21.863 --> 01:26:23.123
[♪ sentimental music playing]

01:26:23.258 --> 01:26:25.034
I... How are you?

01:26:26.973 --> 01:26:28.535
I'm sorry, I should have called

01:26:28.670 --> 01:26:30.676
after the attack
at the White House.

01:26:30.812 --> 01:26:32.216
Are you okay?

01:26:32.352 --> 01:26:33.347
Oh...

01:26:33.850 --> 01:26:35.017
I'm fine.

01:26:35.420 --> 01:26:37.928
It's really good
to hear your voice.

01:26:39.766 --> 01:26:41.430
I didn't think you'd answer.

01:26:42.601 --> 01:26:47.309
Betty, I... I know I've made
a lot of mistakes.

01:26:48.613 --> 01:26:54.158
But I'm trying to change,
to be a better person.

01:26:55.464 --> 01:26:56.493
Um...

01:26:57.430 --> 01:27:01.937
Maybe we could take a...
a walk sometime?

01:27:02.574 --> 01:27:08.054
See the cherry blossoms,
like the old days.

01:27:11.455 --> 01:27:15.299
Yeah. That could be nice.

01:27:17.432 --> 01:27:20.772
Okay. I love you.

01:27:21.483 --> 01:27:22.809
Bye, Dad.

01:27:31.098 --> 01:27:33.335
[reporters chattering]

01:27:43.185 --> 01:27:44.291
Please.

01:27:45.127 --> 01:27:46.890
Good afternoon, everyone.

01:27:49.971 --> 01:27:51.372
When I took office,

01:27:51.507 --> 01:27:57.043
I promised we would create
a true, lasting peace.

01:27:57.881 --> 01:28:02.261
Today, we begin
to realize that promise.

01:28:03.658 --> 01:28:05.333
[Sterns] Captain America...

01:28:08.074 --> 01:28:09.507
would you do me the kindness

01:28:09.642 --> 01:28:13.675
of counseling a bitter man
at the end of his rope?

01:28:13.812 --> 01:28:15.816
That's what you do, isn't it?

01:28:16.828 --> 01:28:18.095
Guess we have five minutes

01:28:18.230 --> 01:28:19.990
until the MPs drag your ass
outta here.

01:28:20.125 --> 01:28:23.599
You ruined my grand finale
on the Indian Ocean.

01:28:23.734 --> 01:28:25.675
So now I'm forced
to turn myself in

01:28:25.812 --> 01:28:27.078
to get what I want.

01:28:27.214 --> 01:28:29.013
Well, if you're waitin'
for an apology,

01:28:29.148 --> 01:28:30.478
we'll be here awhile.

01:28:30.614 --> 01:28:32.187
I'm waiting for you to realize

01:28:32.322 --> 01:28:34.553
that we both want
the same thing,

01:28:34.923 --> 01:28:37.229
for the world to see Ross
as he truly is.

01:28:37.698 --> 01:28:42.643
I'm proud to say our treaty
will finally be signed.

01:28:43.013 --> 01:28:44.746
I'll take a couple questions.

01:28:45.183 --> 01:28:46.447
Sir, what do you say to reports

01:28:46.582 --> 01:28:48.446
that relations with Japan
broke down

01:28:48.581 --> 01:28:49.850
over your handling

01:28:49.986 --> 01:28:51.260
of the White House
assassination attempt?

01:28:51.395 --> 01:28:53.998
Despite fabrications
that some have used

01:28:54.134 --> 01:28:55.869
to turn us against each other,

01:28:56.006 --> 01:28:58.975
our bonds have proved strong.

01:28:59.111 --> 01:29:01.607
You kept Ross alive for years.

01:29:02.244 --> 01:29:05.255
Didn't kill him when you had
the chance at the White House.

01:29:06.419 --> 01:29:08.054
The way I see it,

01:29:08.991 --> 01:29:12.302
the Indian Ocean
wasn't about starting a war.

01:29:13.405 --> 01:29:15.473
You wanted to
destroy his legacy.

01:29:16.470 --> 01:29:17.840
Yes.

01:29:19.008 --> 01:29:20.751
But you haven't figured out how.

01:29:20.886 --> 01:29:22.252
The pills.

01:29:22.387 --> 01:29:24.117
I got somebody on that too.

01:29:24.720 --> 01:29:26.357
Not anymore, you don't.

01:29:27.026 --> 01:29:28.993
Is it true hostilities
in the Indian Ocean

01:29:29.129 --> 01:29:31.006
occurred because
the Japanese discovered

01:29:31.142 --> 01:29:32.505
it was, in fact, your government

01:29:32.641 --> 01:29:34.638
who paid for the SERPENT
mercenary group

01:29:34.774 --> 01:29:36.482
to steal their adamantium?

01:29:37.251 --> 01:29:38.845
We did not pay them.

01:29:38.981 --> 01:29:40.917
Ross turned me into a monster.

01:29:41.287 --> 01:29:44.366
It's only right that I do
the same thing to him.

01:29:45.168 --> 01:29:46.595
Why aren't you smiling?

01:29:46.964 --> 01:29:49.100
- On the ground!
- Hold it!

01:29:54.112 --> 01:29:55.553
You ever use
that big brain of yours

01:29:55.688 --> 01:29:59.087
to consider that maybe
you're wrong about Ross?

01:29:59.524 --> 01:30:00.457
Wanna bet?

01:30:00.592 --> 01:30:01.532
[Sam] Yeah.

01:30:02.736 --> 01:30:05.132
- [Sterns] Where are you going?
- To stop this.

01:30:05.945 --> 01:30:07.610
Get on the ground, now.

01:30:09.011 --> 01:30:10.345
You have the right
to remain silent...

01:30:10.480 --> 01:30:11.647
Captain America!

01:30:12.116 --> 01:30:16.256
If I'm right about Ross,
you're going to die.

01:30:16.725 --> 01:30:18.292
You're going to die!

01:30:19.095 --> 01:30:21.731
Mr. President,
Dr. Samuel Sterns

01:30:21.867 --> 01:30:23.538
just turned himself in.

01:30:23.974 --> 01:30:25.713
He claims you
promised him a pardon

01:30:25.849 --> 01:30:28.518
if he worked on secret
government projects for you.

01:30:28.654 --> 01:30:30.048
- That is a lie.
- [reporters murmuring]

01:30:30.184 --> 01:30:31.851
[Sterns through speaker]
President Ross,

01:30:31.987 --> 01:30:33.365
I miss our little visits.

01:30:33.500 --> 01:30:35.134
[Ross through speaker]
What do you want?

01:30:35.269 --> 01:30:36.732
[Sterns]
I wanted my life back,

01:30:36.868 --> 01:30:38.234
but it's too late for that now.

01:30:38.370 --> 01:30:39.476
Sir...

01:30:39.611 --> 01:30:40.638
[Ross] I helped you
more than anyone else.

01:30:40.773 --> 01:30:41.980
Well, let me explain.

01:30:42.115 --> 01:30:43.317
They have to know.

01:30:43.453 --> 01:30:45.048
[Ross] You gotta
understand my position.

01:30:45.183 --> 01:30:48.762
[Sterns] Oh, I do.
You let me rot in this prison.

01:30:48.897 --> 01:30:50.156
Leave me alone!

01:30:50.291 --> 01:30:52.066
- Leave me! Let me go!
- [Leila] Sir! Sir!

01:30:52.201 --> 01:30:53.437
I cannot let you.

01:30:53.573 --> 01:30:55.476
- You can't let me? Let me?
- I cannot...

01:30:55.611 --> 01:30:59.349
[Sterns] Everyone will know
just who you are.

01:30:59.485 --> 01:31:01.788
And Betty will despise you
even more.

01:31:01.923 --> 01:31:03.583
Sir, please.

01:31:03.718 --> 01:31:05.627
[shouting]

01:31:13.474 --> 01:31:14.546
[agent] Sir.

01:31:19.915 --> 01:31:20.826
[Ross groaning]

01:31:20.961 --> 01:31:22.488
Oh, my God.

01:31:22.624 --> 01:31:24.962
[Ross growling]

01:31:31.071 --> 01:31:32.515
[reporters clamoring]

01:31:40.901 --> 01:31:43.235
[roars]

01:31:43.371 --> 01:31:44.965
Since when were they red?

01:31:45.101 --> 01:31:47.512
[♪ ominous music playing]

01:31:50.316 --> 01:31:51.712
President Ross?

01:31:51.847 --> 01:31:54.516
[growls, grunts]

01:31:55.153 --> 01:31:56.596
Agent Taylor, do we fire?

01:32:03.011 --> 01:32:04.513
[roars]

01:32:05.909 --> 01:32:07.211
[reporters scream]

01:32:32.899 --> 01:32:34.738
This is what Sterns wanted.

01:32:44.654 --> 01:32:45.727
Jesus.

01:32:51.533 --> 01:32:53.174
Sam, I gotta get these people
outta here.

01:32:53.309 --> 01:32:54.538
[Captain America] Set a perimeter
around the White House.

01:32:54.674 --> 01:32:56.078
[roars]

01:33:16.081 --> 01:33:17.549
[Sam grunts]

01:33:20.496 --> 01:33:21.832
[gunfire]

01:33:23.163 --> 01:33:24.239
[Captain America] No.

01:33:24.374 --> 01:33:26.336
Fall back. Fall back!

01:33:32.949 --> 01:33:34.220
Get down!

01:33:36.597 --> 01:33:38.261
[Ruth] Sam, drones incoming.

01:34:17.939 --> 01:34:20.543
[roars]

01:34:22.891 --> 01:34:24.920
Ruth, I need you to
clear Hains Point.

01:34:25.055 --> 01:34:26.356
I'll lure Ross there.

01:34:26.492 --> 01:34:28.795
[Ruth] Sam, are you crazy?
He'll kill you.

01:34:28.931 --> 01:34:30.266
[Captain America] Do it!

01:35:24.909 --> 01:35:27.047
[Ross grunting]

01:35:27.183 --> 01:35:29.213
You can still fight this, Ross.

01:35:29.349 --> 01:35:31.222
Do you see where you are?

01:35:33.455 --> 01:35:35.022
You remember this place?

01:35:35.926 --> 01:35:38.236
You used to come here
with Betty.

01:35:38.705 --> 01:35:39.866
[roars]

01:35:41.272 --> 01:35:42.608
That didn't work.

01:35:51.224 --> 01:35:52.158
Okay.

01:35:52.293 --> 01:35:53.597
You want me?

01:35:54.804 --> 01:35:56.132
Come and get me!

01:35:56.636 --> 01:35:58.772
[♪ dramatic music playing]

01:36:19.347 --> 01:36:21.619
[grunts, groans]

01:36:52.150 --> 01:36:53.148
[boosters pulsing]

01:36:53.283 --> 01:36:54.784
[grunting]

01:36:57.126 --> 01:36:58.859
[boosters fade]

01:37:10.482 --> 01:37:11.885
[straining]

01:37:44.589 --> 01:37:46.923
[Ruth] Sam?
Sam, can you hear me?

01:37:47.460 --> 01:37:48.958
[Leila] Sam, are you okay?

01:37:55.645 --> 01:37:58.046
Please tell me I knocked
that son of a bitch out.

01:37:58.182 --> 01:38:00.520
[sirens wailing]

01:38:02.321 --> 01:38:03.889
[crash]

01:38:05.062 --> 01:38:06.092
Shit.

01:38:11.574 --> 01:38:13.004
Backup's five minutes away.

01:38:13.141 --> 01:38:15.245
[straining]
No, tell them wait.

01:38:15.380 --> 01:38:16.849
What?

01:38:20.362 --> 01:38:21.859
[♪ ominous music playing]

01:38:26.373 --> 01:38:27.701
Should've taken that serum.

01:38:27.836 --> 01:38:29.846
Bucky is full of shit.

01:38:29.982 --> 01:38:31.483
[Ross growls]

01:38:34.223 --> 01:38:35.821
I'm gonna lose that bet.

01:38:43.006 --> 01:38:44.201
Ross.

01:38:44.337 --> 01:38:47.014
We both know you can
take me out with one punch,

01:38:47.517 --> 01:38:49.519
but I don't think
you wanna do that.

01:38:56.866 --> 01:39:00.133
I know you've done
some terrible things.

01:39:01.838 --> 01:39:03.448
Now, I might be crazy...

01:39:04.452 --> 01:39:06.886
but I think you're
trying to change.

01:39:07.690 --> 01:39:09.922
Now's the time to prove it
to the world.

01:39:10.822 --> 01:39:12.225
Prove it to Betty.

01:39:12.895 --> 01:39:15.637
[♪ sentimental music playing]

01:40:07.337 --> 01:40:10.482
The army is transferring
Sterns to a secure facility.

01:40:11.619 --> 01:40:13.215
We should get you
to the hospital.

01:40:14.085 --> 01:40:16.527
There's somewhere
we gotta go first.

01:40:19.666 --> 01:40:21.901
[♪ uplifting music playing]

01:40:28.649 --> 01:40:30.214
That's three, old man.

01:40:32.283 --> 01:40:33.859
I told you I'd get you out.

01:40:34.626 --> 01:40:35.966
Took you so long?

01:40:36.101 --> 01:40:37.635
[chuckles]

01:40:40.340 --> 01:40:41.676
Thank you, Sam.

01:40:42.113 --> 01:40:43.106
I got you.

01:40:43.242 --> 01:40:45.277
I have a few broken bones, so...

01:40:45.679 --> 01:40:46.951
[laughs]

01:40:48.821 --> 01:40:50.055
Come on, Mr. Bradley.

01:40:50.191 --> 01:40:52.298
We got a little paperwork
to fill out,

01:40:52.433 --> 01:40:54.526
and then you're free to go.

01:41:00.783 --> 01:41:02.279
[reporter on TV]
Worldwide talks continue

01:41:02.414 --> 01:41:05.185
in the arms race for
the new discovered element

01:41:05.320 --> 01:41:08.654
as we enter the
brave new world of adamantium.

01:41:08.789 --> 01:41:10.932
Back in our nation's capital,
ground was broken

01:41:11.068 --> 01:41:13.035
on the restoration
of the White House,

01:41:13.171 --> 01:41:15.936
marking a significant step
towards normalcy

01:41:16.071 --> 01:41:17.011
for the country.

01:41:35.483 --> 01:41:36.753
Right this way.

01:41:44.605 --> 01:41:48.711
Mr. President.
How're your digs?

01:41:56.055 --> 01:41:58.225
Intentionally uncomfortable.

01:41:59.396 --> 01:42:01.570
I heard the food
hasn't got any better either.

01:42:01.705 --> 01:42:03.840
- You heard right.
- [chuckles]

01:42:04.442 --> 01:42:05.573
Bradley got out?

01:42:05.708 --> 01:42:06.837
Yes, sir.

01:42:07.173 --> 01:42:08.308
That's good.

01:42:08.643 --> 01:42:10.579
Mr. President,
about your blood work.

01:42:10.714 --> 01:42:13.217
It seems Sterns raised
the level of gamma

01:42:13.353 --> 01:42:15.025
in those pills over time.

01:42:15.162 --> 01:42:17.697
It built up in your body
over the years.

01:42:17.833 --> 01:42:18.667
That led to your...

01:42:18.803 --> 01:42:20.473
Led to my little tantrum.

01:42:20.876 --> 01:42:23.110
Which is why I have to be
in here.

01:42:25.045 --> 01:42:27.253
Good solid walls, these.

01:42:27.388 --> 01:42:28.450
Yeah.

01:42:29.019 --> 01:42:30.359
But I have to say,

01:42:30.728 --> 01:42:31.895
it wasn't nothin' to see you

01:42:32.031 --> 01:42:34.766
take full responsibility
for your actions.

01:42:35.269 --> 01:42:39.370
Give up your office.
Accept your sentence.

01:42:39.505 --> 01:42:41.543
I had to let the country
move on.

01:42:42.514 --> 01:42:44.979
Japan decided to uphold
the treaty, by the way.

01:42:45.115 --> 01:42:46.023
Us too.

01:42:46.759 --> 01:42:49.062
The Ozaki-Ross Accords.

01:42:49.664 --> 01:42:50.925
You did it.

01:42:51.395 --> 01:42:53.136
Sam, why are you here?

01:42:54.200 --> 01:42:55.240
[Sam] Sir?

01:42:56.949 --> 01:42:58.747
We were on different sides
of this thing

01:42:58.882 --> 01:43:00.349
every step of the way.

01:43:02.025 --> 01:43:04.158
Look, if we can't see
the good in each other,

01:43:05.226 --> 01:43:06.999
we've already lost the fight.

01:43:08.370 --> 01:43:11.976
Besides, I wanted to make sure
an old soldier was okay.

01:43:14.173 --> 01:43:17.988
I'd love to stay, but looks
like you have another visitor.

01:43:27.133 --> 01:43:28.305
Hi, Dad.

01:43:32.043 --> 01:43:35.716
I guess I have to give you
a raincheck on that walk.

01:43:36.824 --> 01:43:38.193
It's all right.

01:43:39.992 --> 01:43:42.466
We could just sit and talk
for a little while.

01:43:44.478 --> 01:43:45.868
I'd like that.

01:43:47.415 --> 01:43:48.775
Me too.

01:44:02.009 --> 01:44:03.343
How's the kid doin' today?

01:44:03.478 --> 01:44:06.844
He's still a little out of it
but doin' better.

01:44:07.848 --> 01:44:09.123
I'm gonna let you two catch up.

01:44:09.258 --> 01:44:11.490
Hey, where you headed?
Back to Baltimore?

01:44:11.893 --> 01:44:12.930
No.

01:44:13.567 --> 01:44:16.939
I got Ruth and me tickets
for tonight's game, courtside.

01:44:17.341 --> 01:44:19.406
It's the least I could do
for gettin' me out.

01:44:19.542 --> 01:44:21.114
You know,
I'm happy you found a friend

01:44:21.249 --> 01:44:23.382
as grumpy as you are
to go to games with.

01:44:25.659 --> 01:44:26.884
Say it again.

01:44:28.290 --> 01:44:29.631
[Sam stammers]

01:44:30.000 --> 01:44:32.830
[chuckling] I'm playing.
Got you.

01:44:34.744 --> 01:44:36.838
[EKG machine beeping]

01:44:38.608 --> 01:44:41.253
The Falcon awakens.

01:44:42.852 --> 01:44:44.358
Couldn't let you
have all the fun.

01:44:49.840 --> 01:44:51.809
I'm sorry I screwed up.

01:44:51.944 --> 01:44:53.743
Screwed up? Get out of here.

01:44:53.878 --> 01:44:55.045
I did.

01:44:55.448 --> 01:44:57.153
You never messed up like I have.

01:44:58.190 --> 01:44:59.949
You never got
shot out of the sky

01:45:00.084 --> 01:45:03.297
and nosedived into
the Indian Ocean.

01:45:04.033 --> 01:45:05.501
You're always on point.

01:45:05.637 --> 01:45:06.898
[scoffs]

01:45:07.575 --> 01:45:08.803
Yeah.

01:45:10.641 --> 01:45:12.546
Because if I'm not on point...

01:45:16.795 --> 01:45:18.252
I feel like I let down

01:45:18.388 --> 01:45:21.025
everyone else who was fightin'
for a seat at that table.

01:45:23.875 --> 01:45:25.837
That's pressure, man.

01:45:27.672 --> 01:45:29.250
It weighs on you.

01:45:32.248 --> 01:45:35.086
Makes you wonder
if you'll ever just be...

01:45:36.865 --> 01:45:38.301
enough.

01:45:47.546 --> 01:45:48.585
Where I grew up,

01:45:49.688 --> 01:45:52.330
I only ever got
to see heroes online.

01:45:52.699 --> 01:45:54.201
Or on TV.

01:45:55.631 --> 01:45:57.340
It always felt so far away.

01:45:58.411 --> 01:46:01.138
And I kept thinkin' maybe
if I get out of Miami,

01:46:02.242 --> 01:46:03.719
you know,
maybe one day I could be...

01:46:03.854 --> 01:46:05.522
Don't say Ant-Man.

01:46:05.658 --> 01:46:07.425
[laughs]

01:46:08.856 --> 01:46:10.563
- No, man.
- [chuckles]

01:46:14.635 --> 01:46:16.002
I wanted to be you.

01:46:17.407 --> 01:46:18.046
Well...

01:46:18.181 --> 01:46:19.649
[Joaquin] Sam Wilson.

01:46:20.686 --> 01:46:25.153
Because that guy?
That guy won't ever give up.

01:46:26.992 --> 01:46:28.592
That pressure,
that responsibility

01:46:28.727 --> 01:46:29.801
you talk about?

01:46:30.304 --> 01:46:32.244
I want that too, man.

01:46:41.430 --> 01:46:43.425
You know it's all
about timin', right?

01:46:44.395 --> 01:46:49.234
Control your spin, then hit
your thruster before you kick.

01:46:53.417 --> 01:46:55.683
- No.
- [gasps] Yeah.

01:46:55.818 --> 01:46:57.316
- No. That's...
- [laughs]

01:46:57.752 --> 01:46:58.828
That's it.

01:46:59.599 --> 01:47:01.526
I should get shot out
of the sky more often.

01:47:01.661 --> 01:47:02.829
Yeah, you will.

01:47:02.965 --> 01:47:05.071
- Okay. [chuckles]
- [laughs]

01:47:05.808 --> 01:47:08.239
You know, you're gonna
come back from this.

01:47:08.718 --> 01:47:09.716
I know.

01:47:10.854 --> 01:47:15.185
And when that time comes,
make sure the suit's ready,

01:47:15.322 --> 01:47:17.598
'cause Ross was right
about one thing.

01:47:18.369 --> 01:47:20.698
The world needs the Avengers.

01:47:20.834 --> 01:47:22.944
- For real?
- Yeah.

01:47:23.079 --> 01:47:24.942
Hell, yeah. [chuckles]

01:47:26.387 --> 01:47:27.484
I wasn't thinking
about it before,

01:47:27.619 --> 01:47:29.514
but now that you bring it up...

01:47:29.650 --> 01:47:30.754
Oh, boy.

01:47:30.889 --> 01:47:32.088
...since the wings
are damaged,

01:47:32.224 --> 01:47:33.632
I was thinking, I'm like,
what could make...

01:47:33.768 --> 01:47:34.691
No.

01:47:34.826 --> 01:47:36.330
You didn't hear

01:47:36.466 --> 01:47:37.835
- what I was gonna ask you.
- No. Whatever you ask, nope.

01:47:37.971 --> 01:47:39.869
I'm just saying,
maybe you have, like,

01:47:40.004 --> 01:47:41.508
the Wakandans on speed dial

01:47:41.644 --> 01:47:42.647
and could get me some...

01:47:42.782 --> 01:47:46.625
A hookup on an upgrade
on the wings.

01:47:47.629 --> 01:47:50.325
You're gonna ask the Wakandans
for a hookup?

01:47:50.461 --> 01:47:51.567
Yeah.

01:47:51.702 --> 01:47:53.296
That is the most Miami thing
in the world.

01:47:53.432 --> 01:47:55.533
Are you kidding? They gonna
hook me up, man. Yo.

01:47:55.669 --> 01:47:59.109
[♪ uplifting hip hop,
Kendrick Lamar "i" playing]

01:57:20.060 --> 01:57:20.829
[gate closes]

01:57:20.965 --> 01:57:23.201
[♪ tense music playing]

01:57:27.012 --> 01:57:29.015
Told you you were gonna
lose that bet.

01:57:30.357 --> 01:57:31.722
You wanna know what's funny?

01:57:31.858 --> 01:57:34.553
I'm not in the mood
for your jokes.

01:57:34.923 --> 01:57:37.526
You killed a lot of good men
trying to get your revenge.

01:57:37.661 --> 01:57:40.505
Trust me, we don't share
the same sense of humor.

01:57:40.875 --> 01:57:43.409
We share the same world,
don't we?

01:57:44.080 --> 01:57:46.853
This world you would
die to save?

01:57:48.522 --> 01:57:49.687
It's coming.

01:57:50.257 --> 01:57:52.298
I've seen it
in the probabilities,

01:57:52.433 --> 01:57:54.363
seen it plain as day.

01:57:55.300 --> 01:57:58.338
All you heroes
protecting this world,

01:57:59.242 --> 01:58:01.277
do you think
you're the only ones?

01:58:02.215 --> 01:58:05.021
Do you think
this is the only world?

01:58:06.428 --> 01:58:07.831
We'll see what happens

01:58:07.966 --> 01:58:12.266
when you have to protect
this place from the others.

01:58:13.336 --> 01:58:16.780
[♪ dramatic music crescendos,
fades]
